column3: The Subject Property is a 24,852-square Foot Multi-tenant Retail Strip Center Situated on 2.34-acres in Chester, California.​ More Specifically, the Property is Located Along State Highway 36 Next to Lake Almanor in Plumas County.​ Constructed in 2008, the Property Has Never Been Occupied by Any Tenants and is Currently in “cold Shell” Condition.​ Furthermore, the Offering Includes a Pad Development Site Situated With Excellent Visibility Along Highway 36.​ The “l Shaped” Building Consists of 14 Suites That Can Easily Be Combined.​ Amenities Include a Full Fire Sprinkler Suppression System, Large Porches With Storefront Glass, a Large Monument Sign, and a Lighted Parking Lot.​ A Small Portion of the Roof Has Collapsed Causing Dry Rot and Mold Within the Collapsed Portion of the Building.​ Located in Northwestern Plumas County, Lake Almanor is Located at the Boundary of the Cascade and Sierra Nevada Geologic Provinces, South of Lassen Volcanic National Park.​ Known for Water Sports, Lake Almanor is One of the Largest Lakes in Northern California.​ The Main Economic Drivers in the Lake Almanor Recreation Area Include Tourism and Lumber Production.​ The Lake Almanor and Chester Populations Increase Significantly From Spring Through Fall Months Due to the Significant Amount of Tourism That Floods the Area
column4:

column3:
Marcus & Millichap is pleased to present a prime investment at 102 North Pine Street, New Smyrna Beach, FL 32169.​ This property, near Flagler Avenue, offers a substantial 2247 SF of leasable space with access to New Smyrna Beach's 8 million annual visitors.​

With daily traffic over 10,000 vehicles at 20 MPH, it enjoys high visibility and MAJOR Foot Traffic.​ Immediate potential includes leasing vacant spaces and optimizing rents for below-market tenants.​

In a prime location with coastal home values averaging $3 million, it's Class A+ real estate.​ Full occupancy yields impressive annual returns, with room for growth through rent escalations and higher Airbnb occupancy.​

In a thriving market with a one-mile population growing at 2.70% annually and an average household income exceeding $92,000, this property promises success.​ Its low average vacancy rate reflects strong demand for commercial spaces.​

Investors and owner-users can secure this strategic asset in New Smyrna Beach's dynamic market.​ With immediate value-add potential, strong income prospects, and a diversified mixed-use aspect, 102 North Pine Street thrives in a coastal community.​
column4:
• ​

    PRIME LOCATION: Situated on Pine Street with direct access to the highly coveted Flagler Avenue, this property benefits from a prime location that attracts over 8 million annual visitors to New Smyrna Beach. With an impressive daily traffic count exceeding 10,000 vehicles adhering to a posted speed limit of 20MPH, the property maximizes its exposure.

  • ​

    VALUE-ADD OPPORTUNITY: Immediate value enhancement prospects are available through leasing the 2,247 Gross Leasable Area, which includes both a retail unit/Patio and an upstairs cottage that holds zoning and approval for nightly Airbnb use. This mixed-use aspect diversifies the investment, mitigating risk by encompassing both retail and hospitality sectors.

  • ​

    RARE AIRBNB NIGHTLY RENTAL ZONING: A standout feature of this property is its rare zoning for Airbnb nightly rentals, making it a unique and lucrative opportunity in the market.

  • ​

    OWNER-USER POTENTIAL: The property offers immediate potential for owner-users seeking to occupy the ground-floor retail space, realizing their entrepreneurial dreams, while also leasing the additional 2-bed/1-bath cottage upstairs for supplementary income or enjoying a live/work lifestyle.

  • ​

    CLASS A+ REAL ESTATE | FOOT TRAFFIC HUB: Irreplaceable Real Estate positioned near the bustling Flagler Avenue, a hub for foot traffic in New Smyrna Beach. With millions of annual visitors strolling along this renowned avenue, the property enjoys prime exposure to a steady stream of potential customers and patrons, making it an ideal location for businesses seeking maximum visibility and foot traffic-driven success.

  • ​

    STRONG INCOME POTENTIAL: Achieving full occupancy yields an impressive proforma annual net return of $75,945. Additional growth potential exists through annual rent escalations and the prospect of increasing Airbnb occupancy rates beyond 75% throughout the year.

  • ​

    THRIVING MARKET: The property is situated within a thriving market, with a one-mile population growing at a remarkable annual rate of 2.70%, reaffirming its strategic position within a major growth market.

  • ​

    HIGH AVERAGE HOUSEHOLD INCOME: Within a one-mile radius, the average household income surpasses $92,000 annually. The presence of a substantial RETIREE population contributes to the area's economic stability.

  • ​

    MINIMAL VACANCY RATES: The submarket maintains an exceptionally low average vacancy rate of only 1.0%, underscoring the robust demand for commercial spaces within the area.

Lee & Associates, Los Angeles West Inc.​ is pleased to present for sale 11201-11223 National Boulevard, a highly-visible neighborhood center located at the signalized intersection of major thoroughfare Sepulveda Boulevard and National Boulevard in the heart of West Los Angeles.​

11201-11223 National Boulevard is made up of  approximately 10,883-square foot building (± 11,225 SF per tax record) on approximately 24,400-square feet of  land.​ The property is 100% leased with multiple long-term tenants.​ The site offer tremendous street visibility, and prominent pylon signage,  with a traffic flow of ±34,419 cars per day.​ In addition, there are two income-producing billboards, newsstand, and ATM machine.​ The parking lot is striped for 25 cars and offers immediate ingress and egress to the 405 Freeway at National Boulevard.​

The property is centrally located in the heart of  West Los Angeles, along major arterial Sepulveda Boulevard that travels across the City from the San Fernando Valley all the way to the South Bay.​ The location is amenity rich with ample major retailers like Ross, I-Hop, Von’s, CVS, Subway, Ralph’s and Staples that service the dense residential neighborhoods surrounding the offering.​

11201-11223 National Boulevard is a rare opportunity to purchase a neighborhood retail center well-situated in prime West LA offering stabilized income with low maintenance and ideal for both investors and 1031-exchange buyers.​

column3:
Marcus & Millichap is pleased to exclusively present for your acquisition review 1300 Block Main Street located in Speedway, IN.​

The brand-new 8,600+ square foot building is positioned along Main Street in Indianapolis.​ Speedway has quickly grown into a popular destination for the local population and regional visitors alike.​ The building lies in the shadow of the Indianapolis Motor Speedway, home of The Greatest Spectacle in Racing: the Indy 500.​ During this event, Main Street will see more than a quarter of a million visitors.​  Main Street is home to several racing industry headquarters, Prax Air, Big Woods, Charlie Brown’s, and many other local favorites.​ The delivery of several apartment buildings along main street will continue to increase the need for retail and office demand in the area.​

The property is 100 percent occupied by B.​ Erin Designs LLC, Le Peep, and Vine & Table.​  All three tenants signed fresh ten-year leases, which commenced on May 1, 2023, leaving more than nine and a half years of lease term remaining for each tenant.​  B.​Erin Designs has a rent increase in year three and in year seven of their base term.​  Le Peep and Vine & Table both have rent increases in year six of their base terms.​  The rent increases provide rent growth and a strong hedge against potential inflation.​  The leases are triple net, with each tenant being financially responsible for their pro rata share of all common area maintenance, real estate taxes, insurance and a partial administration fee reimbursement as well.​  The Home Owners Association is responsible for the management of all common area maintenance, offering a future landlord a passive, relatively hands-free investment.​

Le Peep and Vine & Table are two tenants that have been very popular in the Indianapolis area for 20+ years.​ Le Peep is a breakfast, brunch, and lunch restaurant that has been voted the #1 breakfast & brunch restaurant by the Dallas Observer, Denver Post, Denver Rocky Mountain News, Houston Post, Dallas Morning News, Indianapolis Star, and more.​ Le Peep can be found in Colorado, Florida, Idaho, Illinois, Indiana, Missouri, north Carolina, Nebraska, New Jersey, Ohio, South Carolina, Tennessee, and Texas.​ Vine & Table has been offering the finest wines, spirits, and craft beers in Indiana since 1996.​ This location will be the third location that Vine & Table has opened in the Indianapolis area.​

column2: Prime Investment Opportunity: Multi-Tenant Building Property for Sale in the heart of Alvin
column3:
Welcome to Gordon Street Plaza: Alvin's Charming Neighborhood Shopping Center

Location: Gordon Street, Alvin, TX

Nestled on the bustling Gordon Street that runs through the heart of Alvin, Texas, Gordon Street Plaza is a beloved neighborhood shopping center that has been a cornerstone of the community since 1981.​ This 5,550 square foot commercial gem is the perfect blend of convenience, history, and modern amenities.​

Community Hub:

Gordon Street Plaza isn't just a shopping center; it's the beating heart of the Alvin community.​ With three dedicated entrances, it seamlessly connects the town's residents with their favorite local businesses.​ This well-designed layout offers convenience and accessibility, making it a go-to destination for both regular patrons and newcomers.​

Long-Standing Tenants:

Two of the three spaces in Gordon Street Plaza have been occupied by cherished local businesses for many years.​ These tenants have not only become integral parts of the community but also add to the center's warm and welcoming atmosphere.​ The longstanding presence of these businesses is a testament to the strong sense of community and loyalty that defines Alvin.​

Modern Comfort and Convenience:

Despite its historic roots, Gordon Street Plaza is equipped with all the modern conveniences you'd expect from a contemporary shopping center.​ The spacious 5,550 square feet of retail space provides ample room for businesses to thrive, while the concrete parking lot ensures hassle-free parking for visitors.​

Retail Variety:

Gordon Street Plaza is home to a diverse range of businesses, catering to the needs and tastes of Alvin's residents.​ From local boutiques to essential services, you'll find a variety of options within its walls, making it a one-stop destination for shopping, dining, and more.​

A Piece of Alvin's History:

Built in 1981, Gordon Street Plaza is not just a shopping center; it's a piece of Alvin's history.​ Its timeless design and enduring presence on Gordon Street make it a beloved landmark for both residents and visitors.​

Join Our Community:

Gordon Street Plaza welcomes new businesses to join our vibrant community and become part of Alvin's rich tapestry.​ With dedicated entrances, loyal patrons, and a prime location on the main street, your business can thrive in this welcoming environment.​

Gordon Street Plaza: Where history meets modern convenience, and community is at the core.​ Come and experience the charm of Alvin's beloved neighborhood shopping center.​
column4:
1. ​

    Steady Rental Income: Gordon Street Plaza enjoys consistent rental income from its long-standing tenants, providing investors with a stable and reliable revenue stream.

  2. ​

    Prime Location: Situated on Gordon Street, a main thoroughfare in Alvin, the shopping center benefits from high visibility and a constant flow of traffic, increasing the potential for foot traffic and customer exposure.

  3. ​

    Diverse Tenant Mix: With a variety of businesses, including established local boutiques and essential services, Gordon Street Plaza offers a diverse tenant mix that appeals to a broad range of customers, reducing the risk associated with relying on a single industry.

  4. ​

    Strong Community Ties: The shopping center's tenants have built strong community ties over the years, fostering a sense of loyalty among local customers and ensuring a consistent customer base.

  5. ​

    Historic Charm: Gordon Street Plaza, built in 1981, combines historical charm with modern amenities, making it an attractive destination for businesses and customers alike.

  6. ​

    Room for Growth: With one space currently available for lease, there is potential for additional rental income and the opportunity to attract a new business that complements the existing tenant mix.

  7. ​

    Concrete Parking Lot: The presence of a concrete parking lot enhances the shopping center's appeal, providing convenience for both tenants and customers.

  8. ​

    Proximity to Residential Areas: Alvin's residential neighborhoods surround Gordon Street Plaza, making it a convenient shopping destination for the local population.

  9. ​

    Investment in Alvin's Future: Investing in Gordon Street Plaza means investing in the growth and sustainability of the Alvin community, which is poised for future development and prosperity.

column3: Marcus & Millichap’s Brown Retail Group has been selected to exclusively market for sale 192nd Plaza, a newly developed retail center located in rapidly growing Camas, WA (Portland/Vancouver MSA).​ The Property is currently 92.4% occupied with pending LOIs on two vacant suites, which the Seller will guarantee for two years post-closing.​ Nearly 80% of the GLA has occupied the Property for more than 6 years.​ The Seller's current loan, fixed at a 5.00% interest rate until March, 2026 and amortized over 30 years, is assumable and features a balance of roughly $6,300,000 (contact listing agent for additional details).​ Regus occupies approximately 42% of the GLA at the Property and is only paying $6.60/SF NNN in rent, with market rents achievable in the $20/SF - $22/SF NNN range, providing an investor with significant upside in increasing rents for this space to market.​ All of the tenants at the Property currently operate on NNN leases allowing for reimbursement of nearly all expenses and providing a hedge against rising operating expenses.​ The Property features a total of eleven tenants with varying lease expiration dates, ensuring long-term occupancy levels.​ The Property was built in 2010, features high-quality finishes and has been maintained in great condition.​ The Property benefits from a population of over 165,000 residents within a 5-mile radius, with average household incomes exceeding $105,000.​ Within a 5-mile radius, the population has grown nearly 20% since 2010 and is projected to increase by another 4.6% in the next 5 years.​ Within a 1-mile radius, the population has grown by more than 36% since 2010.​ Camas, WA submarket rents have increased a cumulative 9.5% over the past three years, per CoStar.​ With only 5.0% retail footprint growth in the past decade and zero square feet of new retail space currently under construction, the development lull creates a high barrier to entry and demand for space remains high.​
column4:
FULLY LEASED RETAIL CENTER WITH STRONG HISTORICAL OCCUPANCY

The Property is currently 92.4% occupied with pending LOIs on two vacant suites, which the Seller will guarantee for two years post-closing. Nearly 80% of the GLA has occupied the Property for more than 6 years.

ATTRACTIVE ASSUMABLE FINANCING AVAILABLE

The Seller's current loan, fixed at a 5.00% interest rate until March, 2026 and amortized over 30 years, is assumable and features a balance of roughly $6,300,000. Contact listing agent for additional details.

BELOW MARKET RENT IN UPSTAIRS REGUS SUITE

Regus occupies approximately 42% of the GLA at the Property and is only paying $6.60/SF NNN in rent, with market rents achievable in the $20/SF - $22/SF NNN range, providing an Investor with significant upside in increasing rents for this space to market.

ATTRACTIVE NNN LEASE STRUCTURE

All of the tenants at the Property currently operate on NNN leases allowing for reimbursement of nearly all expenses and providing a hedge against rising operating expenses.

STAGGERED LEASE EXPIRATION DATES

The Property features a total of eleven tenants with varying lease expiration dates, ensuring long-term occupancy levels. In addition, multiple tenants at the Property have recently expressed interest in extending their lease terms.

HIGH-QUALITY 2010 CONSTRUCTION

The Property was built in 2010, features high-quality finishes and has been maintained in great condition.

STRONG, INCREASING CUSTOMER VISITS

The Property has seen an increase in customer visits by over 20% year-over-year, with over 312,000 visits in the last twelve months, per Placer.ai.

AFFLUENT, HIGH POPULATION GROWTH SUB-MARKET

The Property benefits from a population of over 165,000 residents within a 5-mile radius, with average household incomes exceeding $105,000, well above the national average. Within a 5-mile radius, the population has grown nearly 20% since 2010 and is projected to increase by another 4.6% in the next 5 years. Within a 1-mile radius, the population has grown by more than 36% since 2010.

STRONG RENT GROWTH (9.5%) AND HIGH BARRIER TO ENTRY MARKET

Camas/Washougal Submarket rents have increased a cumulative 9.5% over the past three years, per CoStar. With only 5.0% retail footprint growth in the past decade and zero square feet of new retail space currently under construction, the development lull creates a high barrier to entry and demand for space remains high.

STRATEGIC LOCATION SURROUNDED BY RESIDENTIAL DEVELOPMENT

The Property benefits from being surrounded by residential neighborhoods and apartments, including Westridge Lofts (100 units) and Grandview Place (154 units) directly adjacent to the Property, 192nd West Lofts (169 units) across the street, and Kielo at Grass Valley (276 units) within a quarter mile. The Property also provides services to the employees from the surrounding business campuses, including Fisher Investment’s headquarters and the Vancouver Innovation Center, a 179-acre master-planned campus catering to the high-tech, bio-tech, and light industrial industries.

EXCELLENT RETAIL LOCATION WITH STRONG VISIBILITY TO OVER 26,000 VPD

Located on a signalized, hard-corner with excellent visibility and exposure to over 26,000 VPD on SE 192nd Ave and SE 20th St. with multiple points of ingress and egress.

DIVERSE, SERVICE, AND DAILY NEEDS ORIENTED TENANT MIX

The Property is occupied with a mix of retail, medical, and professional service tenants offering a stable and diversified income stream.

INCOME TAX FREE STATE

Washington State is an income tax free state.

column3:
20 Cosmo Place consists of a standalone restaurant property with 16,395 square feet of leasable area, situated on a 12,880-SF or 0.30-acre site at 20 Cosmo Place near Union Square in San Francisco’s downtown district.​ The location is favorable, lying between Post and Sutter Streets, and the property has frontage on both Cosmo Place (main entrance) and Sutter Street (north).​ The building was constructed around 1921 and stands out for its larger-than-average size, making it one of the city’s notable restaurants in terms of its capacity.​

This legendary culinary destination has been home to two iconic restaurants over the last 68 years.​ From the renowned Trader Vic's (1951-1994) to its current gem, Le Colonial (since 1998), this space embodies a rich tradition of gastronomic excellence.​  It features two kitchens with type 1 hoods on two levels and offers a versatile canvas for culinary creativity.​  With entrances on Cosmo Place, Sutter Streets, and the main entrance on 20 Cosmo, accessibility is a breeze.​ The vintage San Francisco facade adds character and charm, while the 400-seat capacity ensures ample space for patrons.​ A 22-car adjacent parking lot is also available and provides easy delivery access.​ Elevators are in place for seamless vertical transit.​

This investment opportunity seamlessly combines prime location, high visibility, and immediate value enhancement prospects, positioning 300 Flagler Avenue for success in a thriving locale.​

column3:
Exciting Redevelopment Opportunity in Historic Downtown Kapaa, Hi
we Are is Thrilled to Present a Unique Opportunity in the Heart of Downtown Kapaa.​ the Dragon Shopping Center Located at 4504 Kukui St.​ Offering an Exceptional Chance for Investors & Developers to Acquire a Landmark Property Facing Kuhio Hwy, the Primary Arterial Road Connecting the North Shore With the Rest of the Island.​
the Center's Highly Desirable Location on the Center Strip & Adjacent to the Abc Store, Further Enhances Its Appeal.​ With Approximately 14,478 Sqft of Rentable Space, Featuring 4 Deluxe Restrooms & 30 Private Parking Stalls, the Property Boasts Exceptional Amenities.​ It Occupies 17,011 Sqft of Commercial Mix Use Zoned Land in the Downtown Kapaa Business District.​
this Property is Ideally Suited for Partial Conversion Into the Lucrative Residential Market.​ Currently, the Property Has Been Used as Retail/office Space.​ However, Considering the Kapaa Median Residential Sale Price at $1.0m & the Median Rent Reaching $3k Per Month, Converting the Office Space Into Residential Loft Units Would Significantly Increase the Property's Revenue, Value & Provide a Stable Source of Income.​
in Pursuit of This Vision, We Have Taken Initial Steps to Engage With the Planning Department & We Are Delighted to Share That They Have Provided Verbal Approval for Our Plans.​
our Mix Use Zoning Allows Us to Convert the Property Into Residential Lofts While Maintaining the Downstairs Retail Units, Anchored by the Restaurant, Art Gallery.​
in Addition We Have Been Granted Verbal Permission to Create 15 Residential Units.​ Another Significant Benefit of Converting the Top Units Into Residential Spaces is the Substantial Reduction in Parking Requirements.​ This Opens Up More Possibilities Such as Renting Out Excess Parking to Neighboring Buildings That Lack Parking Facilities and Generating Additional Income.​

4th Street Retail Plaza is a 7,025-square-foot, multi-tenant retail center located in a densely populated area of Lubbock, Texas.​ The center is currently 100 percent occupied, and all leases are triple-net.​ Tenants are a complementary mix of internet-resistant businesses including AT&T, Endzone Liquor, and Fancy Nails & Spa.​ AT&T and Endzone Liquor are long-term tenants, having occupied the center for over 22 years and 13 years, respectively.​ The AT&T store has a strong guarantee from the largest AT&T authorized retailer in the nation.​ Endzone Liquor and Fancy Nails & Spa leases both have personal guarantees.​ Originally constructed in 1990, the center is situated on 0.78 acres with concrete parking.​ 

The subject property is located on 4th Street, near the signalized intersection of 4th Street and Frankford Avenue and just west of Loop 289.​ Traffic Counts in front of the property exceed 17,280 vehicles per day on 4th Street.​ The property is near a top performing Walmart Supercenter, ranking in the 82nd percentile based on annual visitors to all Walmart stores in the state of Texas and the 88th percentile in the United States (Source: Placer Labs Inc.​).​ Other retailers in the in the area include Bahama Buck's, Sonic Drive-In, Wendy's, Little Caesars Pizza, Taco Bell, GameStop, Chick-fil-A, Raising Cane's, Dollar Tree, WingStop, Cato, Sally Beauty Supply, Spec's, Whataburger, Slim Chickens, and many others.​ The surrounding area is densely populated with more than 152,244 residents within a five-mile radius.​

Marcus and Millichap is thrilled to present an exceptional investment opportunity: The Sooner Market Place, located at 5500-5540 E Reno Ave.​ This meticulously renovated retail center spans an impressive 63,063 square feet and is situated on a generous 5.93-acre lot.​ Currently, it boasts an outstanding 97% occupancy rate, housing 33 diverse tenants.​ The property offers approximately 490 surface parking spaces and enjoys prime frontage on both E Reno Ave and S Sooner Rd.​

 

Within the center, the individual unit sizes average 1,800 square feet, with the smallest tenant occupying 600 square feet.​ Notably, the largest tenant at The Sooner Market Place is Chelino's Mexican Restaurant, a beloved local establishment with a presence spanning over 12 locations in Oklahoma City and at this site for over 25 years.​ Known for its authentic Mexican cuisine, Chelino's has earned its place as one of Oklahoma's favorite Mexican restaurants, anchoring the largest space at 6,800 square feet.​

 

Notably, current rental rates significantly lag behind market levels, with a weighted average lease term of just 1 year.​ This presents a significant opportunity for an investor to optimize rental income, aligning it with prevailing market rates.​

 

Factoring in an 8% vacancy factor, the initial Capitalization Rate (Cap Rate) stands at an attractive 7.82%.​ Additionally, we've accounted for an additional $471,376 allocated for Tenant Improvements and Leasing Commissions.​ When these enhancements are implemented to bring rents in line with market rates, the property is poised to stabilize at an impressive 12.32% Cap Rate.​

 

The Sooner Market Place is strategically located and promises substantial potential for savvy investors looking to capitalize on this well-positioned retail center.​

column3:
Infill Med-Tail Center with Value-Add Potential – This is an opportunity to acquire a recently redeveloped mixed-use asset on the border of two revitalized neighborhoods; highly dense Fells Point and Canton in Baltimore, Maryland (the “Offering”).​

The Offering includes two leased spaces to national med-tail brands, a vacant second story (cold dark shell) office suite, along with the attractive revenues generated from leased surface parking spaces.​ On the building’s ground floor, Heart + Paw and Phoenix Physical Therapy are the newest occupants after renovations, which have a weighted average lease term remaining of six years and are growing, creditworthy chains.​  

A Variety of Value Enhancement Opportunities – The Offering’s Net Operating Income is based on in-place projections at 68% occupancy.​ The vacancy is a second-story 3,000 square-foot office suite in cold dark shell condition.​ The high ceiling space has the potential for a roof deck.​ Investors may seek to occupy this space as a user, create a separate condominium and sell off the unit, or lease it to stabilize the investment.​  

Investors will also find upside in the parking space revenues which are approximately 13% of the property’s overall gross revenues across a total of 30 leasable spaces.​ This is a high-demand parking area.​ For multiple decades this lot has served as leased parking to users of this site and surrounding businesses.​ With significant development taking place around it, much of the surface parking has been developed vertically including a surface lot immediately across Aliceanna Street.​ Presently, there are nine unleased spaces which could increase the annual income by $16,200.​ Additionally, an investor can continue to raise overall rent rates beyond the current market of $150 per month which has been done recently by ownership.​

Additional Parking Upside - The recent departures of two food-trucks provides upside potential as they occupied a total of three spaces.​ REEF Services was paying $2,000 per month, while a second food truck was paying $300 per month.​ The REEF location has all utilities installed.​ The estimated $16,200 potential from increased parking revenues assumes no new food-trucks are added to the lot.​

Lastly, Ownership is entering into an agreement with S&P+ Parking for ticketing and evening parking via electronic gating and periodic patrol of the lot.​ The revenues from this agreement have not been modeled into projections, but will be shared 50/50 with S&P+ and new ownership over the present base of revenues.​ It is estimated that an owner may benefit from an additional $20,888 per year once this agreement is operational.​

The subject property has fantastic placement on Highway 62 (20,000+ VPD) in order to serve not just the local residents, but also Baxter Health campus physicians and staff, students at Arkansas State University MH, and Mountain Home High School.​ The recent addition of this 7 Brew location is a major benefit to the community, as there are no other standalone national coffee retailers in the city of Mountain Home.​

Avison Young, as exclusive agent is pleased to offer for sale the retail condominium (“the Unit”) located at the base of 74 Grand Street, a newly built 6-story luxury residential condominium located between Greene and Street in the heart of SoHo.​ The Unit is comprised of 1,541 square feet at-grade, 1,094 square foot in the lower level, and a 359 SF rear terrace, for a total of 2,994 gross square feet.​ There is approximately 22 feet of frontage along Grand Street.​ The Unit is currently occupied on a short-term basis by No Standing NYC, a well-known retailer of designer vintage apparel and accessories.​

74 Grand Street is a striking revitalized cast-iron property designed by renowned architect Joseph Pell Lombardi.​ It was developed with the intention of paying homage to its 1885 predecessor with the award-winning restoration of its façade.​ The building has been featured in the New York Times and was the recipient of the 2022 Preservation Award for excellence in restoration, preservation, and adaptive use of a historic building by the New York Landmarks Conservancy.​

74 Grand Street presents investors and users alike with a unique opportunity to acquire a new construction, beautifully restored asset in an evergreen, irreplaceable location.​ The strong co-tenancy in the area brings in consistently high levels of foot traffic and visibility, and would be a strategic location for any brand looking for exposure in one of Manhattan’s hottest retail markets.​

column3:
Welcome to 9405 East Independence Blvd, a premier multi-tenant commercial property strategically positioned on one of the most vibrant and high-traffic corridors in the Charlotte area.​ This exceptional property offers an outstanding investment opportunity in a location surrounded by nationally recognized retailers, presenting a compelling prospect for investors and business owners.​ 

This +/- 12,200 SF building sitting on 0.933 Acres includes two tenants:

 

Plaza Appliance- a reliable tenant since 2016 who occupies 8,100 square feet of prime retail space within the  building with a loading dock in the back.​ With a lease extending through 2026, Plaza Appliance offers stability and consistent rental income for the purchaser.​

 

Infamous Ink- occupies 4,100 square feet of space, meticulously renovated to meet their specific needs, as evident in the attached interior improvement pictures.​ Their lease is valid through 2024, providing a reliable income stream and the possibility for lease renewal in the future.​

 

This property presents an attractive investment opportunity with two stable NNN tenants with annual increases offering immediate rental income.​  As of December 15th, 2023, this piece of property will generate $188,858.04 of NOI.​ 

 

*For buyers looking to occupy the Plaza Appliance space as an owner user, it’s worth noting that Plaza Appliance is willing to vacate the premises within 120 days, facilitating a smooth transition for the new owner to take possession.​

Airline Retail Center is a 12,600-square-foot, multi-tenant retail center located in Bossier City, Louisiana.​ The center is currently 100 percent occupied, and all leases are triple-net.​ Tenants are a complementary mix of service-oriented businesses, including Taqueria La Michoacana, Any Garment Cleaners, Paycheck Loans, Go Auto, Lendmark Financial Services, and Vape Stop.​ Originally constructed in 1997, the building is situated on a 1.63-acre lot with ample paved parking.​ A double-sided monument sign providing additional exposure to the center.​ 

The subject property is located on Airline Drive, approximately one mile north of Interstate 20.​ Traffic counts in front of Airline Retail Center exceed 34,200 vehicles per day.​ The center is located in a dense retail trade area, neighbored by numerous national and regional tenants including The Home Depot, Hobby Lobby, Kroger Marketplace, Walmart Supercenter, Lowe's Home Improvement, Altitude Trampoline Park, Whataburger, Freddy's Frozen Custard & Steakburgers, Raising Cane's, Uptown Cheapskate, Verizon Wireless, PJ's Coffee, Block Advisors, Walgreens, Popeyes, Dirt Cheap, Rent-A-Center, Big Lots, CVS, Office Depot, Harbor Freight Tools, Chili's Grill & Bar, Red Lobster, Taco Bell, Starbucks, Firestone Complete Auto Care, and many others.​ Airline Retail Center is also in close proximity to Pierre Bossier Mall, positioned on the north side of Interstate 20.​  The mall is anchored by JCPenney, Dillard's, and Surge Entertainment by Drew Brees, with other major tenants such as Bath & Body Works, Foot Locker, Forever 21, Hibbett Sports, Shoe Dept.​ Encore, and more.​ The property is less than five miles from Barksdale Airforce Base, serving a population of approximately 14,581 active duty members, reservists, and civilians.​

We are pleased to present a rare opportunity to purchase a two-tenant NNN property occupied by ALDI corporate on a new 10-year lease and Tractor Supply Company corporate with 3 years remaining and a successful history at this property.​ The subject property are the grocery and home improvement anchors to a regional shopping center (Deerfoot Village) which includes additional anchor tenant Bealls

Outlet and serves the entire Bradford County area.​ The property is located in Starke, Florida - the county seat of Bradford County – and a city ideally situated on the major thoroughfare of US-301 halfway between Gainesville (University of Florida) and Jacksonville MSA (30 minutes to each).​ The subject property also benefits from its location directly on US-301/S Walnut St which sees over 33,267 vehicles per day (VPD) directly in front of the site.​

As testament to the location’s status as the ideal retail location in the market, ALDI recently signed a brand new 10-year lease (brand new store) that commenced August of 2022.​ Aldi Süd is a Germany-based company with $23.5B in revenue and operates over 2,100 stores in the US.​ Additionally, Tractor Supply Co has profitably thrived at this location since 2006 and recently exercised a 5-year option to renew their lease.​ They have one 5-year option remaining at which time their rental rate with increase by 10%.​ Tractor Supply Co (NASDAQ: TSCO) operates over 2,000 stores and is a Fortune 500 company with a market cap over $27.3B and an S&P rating of “BBB” (investment grade).​

Starke, FL benefits from its position as the county seat with stable government jobs in administration, a healthy business environment, and higher household incomes than the surrounding areas which equates to stronger tenant performance and increased long-term leasing demand.​ Starke also enjoys strong employment due to its proximity to Florida State Prison and to Camp Blanding Joint Training Center – the primary military reservation and training base for the Florida National Guard (both Army and Air).​

This is a unique opportunity to purchase an excellent NNN property leased to extremely strong national tenants and exceptionally well located with great real estate fundamentals on 7.97 acres of land with future upside.​

NAI Hallmark, as exclusive advisor, is privileged to present the opportunity to acquire Amelia Marketplace located at 474331 State Road 200, Fernandina Beach, Florida (the “Property”).​  The Property consists of a fully leased multi-tenanted retail center totaling 27,909 square feet as well as a ground lease to Elliano’s Coffee.​

The property provides a rare opportunity to purchase a well-located, stabilized retail center with a strong, diversified rent roll in the quickly growing Nassau County and the potential to increase rents to market rate over time.​
column4:
• ​

    STABLE CASHFLOW WITH UPSIDE: The property has a strong rent roll with a diversified tenant mix.  The property is currently fully occupied, but with several tenants paying below market rents, there is room for upside by increasing those tenants to market rate rents.  

  • ​

    IDEAL LOCATION ON MAJOR THOROUGHFARE: The property is strategically located on State Road 200, the main east-west thoroughfare in Nassau County.  The road connects the inland part of the county to Amelia Island, popular amongst tourists and a desirable beach community.  The Property is well positioned at the main entrance to Amelia Island with State Road 200 seeing traffic counts of 49,000 AADT.

  • ​

    STRONG SUBMARKET GROWTH: Nassau County is currently going through a period of exponential growth with the development of the master planned community, Wildlight, underway.  Wildlight will offer 24,000 homes and is located just 7 miles West of the Property on State Road 200.  Nassau County is also home to Amelia Island which has grown in popularity over the past several years both for tourists and residents in the beach community.

  • ​

    ROBUST Retail RENT GROWTH: The Jacksonville MSA has experienced tremendous rent growth, specifically for retail properties, over the past several years.  According to Costar data, Jacksonville led the country in Q2 2023 in retail rent growth at 11.9%.  The Property, with some tenants paying below market rents, and rapid rent growth, is positioned well to add value in the coming years.

CIRE Partners is pleased to exclusively offer for sale this Arby's drive-thru retail center investment located in the City of Orange, California.​ Constructed in 2009, this ±4,240 SF property sits on a lot size of approximately 26,915 SF and boasts a 100% occupancy rate.​ The center is home to a diverse mix of tenants: Arby's, renowned for its drive-thru service, YC Dental Family Dentistry, and Fíala Beauty.​

Set at a corner location, this center offers premier queuing with an efficient drive-thru stack design, accommodating above-standard vehicle stacking (which is greatly desired by QSR tenants), property further features great visibility, monument signage and three (3) access points, standing out prominently in the area.​

Additionally, the building's 2009 construction and consistent maintenance over the years minimize deferred maintenance concerns.​ As current leases inch closer to their expiration, investors are presented with an opportunity to transition to true Triple Net (NNN) leases and improving returns by adjusting rents to market rates.​

Situated on North Tustin St, a key North-South route nearly parallel to the SR 55, the property benefits from robust traffic counts, bolstered by its close proximity to Katella Ave and State Route 55.​ Current proforma estimates spotlight the drive-thru rents as approximately well below the estimated market rate for comparable spaces in Orange County, presenting a lucrative rental adjustment opportunity.​

Veritas Realty is pleased to present an exclusive opportunity to acquire the newly constructed (first-class designed) build to suit two-tenant property, Auburn Shoppes.​ This brand-new McAlister’s Deli and Well Now Urgent Care investment property is perfectly positioned in the heart of this increasingly desirable dominant Northwest Indiana trade area, characterized by retail brokers as one of the tightest (high barrier to entry) retail corridors in the state.​ With steadily growing surrounding employment attracting many young highly educated professionals and benefiting from approx.​ 15 miles to the nearest relevant interstate interchange, this SR 8 (W 7th Street)corridor serves a super-regional trade area and is home to many of the strongest retail and restaurant sales volumes in all of Indiana.​

This property has tremendous access and incredible visibility to SR 8 (W 7th St); it is positioned only 730’ from Interstate 69(nearly 40,000 AVD), less than 1 mile to downtown Auburn nearby proximity to newly developed apartments, manufacturing, car dealerships, and senior living projects, and surrounded by best-in-class regional and national retailers, hotels, medical and restaurants including Walmart Supercenter, Kroger, Home Depot, ALDI, CVS, Ace Hardware, Hampton Inn, Hilton, Holiday Inn, Lutheran Health, DeKalb Hospital, YMCA, Starbucks, Culver’s, McDonald’s, Taco Bell, Wendy’s, Arby’s, KFC, Applebee’s, Buffalo Wild Wings, and Auburn Crossing (17 acre mixed-use retail project under construction with Texas Roadhouse, Chipotle, Verizon and many more).​ In addition, last year Parkview Health (largest employer in Northwest Indiana with more than 14,000) acquired a 77-acres (1/3 of a mile away from Auburn Shoppes) at the northwest quadrant of I-69 & SR 8 (W 7th St) to develop a massive regional healthcare campus.​

Located less than 20 miles from downtown Chicago, the Property beneﬁts from its strategic neighborhood location with more than 100,000 residents in a 3-mile radius.​ This neighborhood retail provides ease and convenience for residents, which has helped Little Tots Daycare thrive for nearly two decades.​

Marcus & Millichap and RI Marketplace are pleased to present the opportunity to acquire the 1018 & 1021-1029 North Water Street in Decatur, Illinois (the “Property”).​ The Property provides the opportunity for a new owner to purchase an easy to manage, two national credit tenant center that provides generous cash flow.​ The Property consists of a single-story building totaling 21,294 SF on a 1.24-acre parcel as well as a surplus parking lot on a separate 0.39-acre parcel.​ The building is 100% occupied by CSL Plasma and the State of Illinois Department of Human Services.​  CSL Plasma has been a tenant since 1996 and completed a $600,000 in improvements a few years ago showing their commitment to the site.​ The State of Illinois moved into the building in 2022 and has a brand-new buildout.​ With only two tenants plus additional billboard income, the asset is perfect for an investor looking for a passive investment.​

Decatur is the largest city and the county seat of Macon County.​ Decatur has an economy based on industrial and agricultural commodity processing and production, including the North American headquarters of agricultural conglomerate Archer Daniels Midland, international agribusiness Tate & Lyle's largest corn-processing plant, and the designing and manufacturing facilities for Caterpillar Inc.​'s wheel-tractor scrapers, compactors, large wheel loaders, mining class motor grader, off-highway trucks, and large mining trucks.​ The Property has excellent frontage on North Water Street with visibility to traffic counts of 11,835 vehicles per day.​ The Property benefits from extremely strong demographics with a 2023 population of ±75,985 and an average household income of ±$63,648 within a 5-mile radius.​

Marcus & Millichap, in conjunction with RI Marketplace, is pleased to offer for sale the fee simple interest in the North Olmsted Retail Center, a 67,050 square foot retail center located on Lorain Road in North Olmsted, Ohio (the "Property”).​ Well located within one of Cleveland’s largest and busiest retail trade areas, the Property presents a strong value-add opportunity for investors to purchase an infill shopping center in a dense & affluent Cleveland west-side suburb.​ The offering provides stable cash flow with the opportunity to quickly enhance NOI through lease-up of vacancy.​  

North Olmsted Retail Center is comprised of two buildings situated on 6.2 acres.​ The first is a 62,550 SF inline shopping center with a junior anchor box leased to Ashley Outlet, and two vacant mid-size inline shop units.​ The second building is a freestanding 4,500 SF building leased to Vitamin Shoppe, located at the front of the parcel with direct frontage and visibility to Lorain Road.​  Ashley Outlet signed a new seven-year gross lease on the 43,435-square foot box in 2022.​ Vitamin Shoppe has been in-place since 2003 and is leased to NNN terms.​ The weighted average lease term remaining of the occupied GLA is 5.2 years.​ Significant upside can be realized via successful lease-up of the two adjacent inline vacancies totaling 16,615 square feet.​

North Olmsted, Ohio is home to 5.6 million square feet of retail leased to 98% occupancy, with key traffic-driving assets including Great Northern Mall & Great Northern Plaza, which feature notable tenants Home Depot, Macy’s, Dillard’s, JCPenney, Best Buy, Dick’s Sporting Goods, Burlington, Big Lots, JOANN, PetSmart, and more.​ Other major retailers in the trade area include Walmart, Target, Giant Eagle, Aldi, Value City Furniture, Harbor Freight, Bob’s Discount Furniture, and dozens of national restaurant chains.​ The area is bolstered by several hotels, office buildings, and multifamily apartment complexes, as well as its immediate proximity to Cleveland’s major international airport (Hopkins).​ Demographics in the area are dense with nearly 65,000 residents in a three-mile radius and 173,000 residents in a five-mile radius, and household incomes are above-average ranging from $85,000 to $102,000 within one-, three-, and five-mile radii.​ Lorain Road, which the Property is located along, is a major east-west arterial spanning from Downtown Cleveland into neighboring Lorain County, and additional traffic to the area generates from the major I-480 interchange at Great Northern Boulevard and Brookpark Road, the latter of which merges into Lorain Road directly in front of the Property.​

column2: Value-Add / Redevelopment Opportunity - Pad Development - Below Replacement Cost
column3:
Significant Redevelopment/Value-Add Opportunity With In-Place Cash Flow:

• Base Line Shopping Center is an ±49,045 Square ft.​ Neighborhood Center on ±5.7 Acres Providing a Near Term Redevelopment Opportunity With In-Place Cash Flow.​

• Absence of CC&Rs and Existing Multi-Parcel Site Provides New Ownership With the Opportunity for Future Break-Up Sale Strategy.​

• Significant Capital Improvements made to the Roof, Edifice and Interior Infrastructure of Main Anchor Space.​

• Prominent 40 ft.​ Tall Pylon Sign on Base Line Street Bolsters Tenant Visibility and Branding Opportunities.​

• Attractive Basis at $111 Per Square ft.​ (Significantly Below Replacement Cost).​

• Existing Leases Provide New Ownership With Flexible Landlord Termination Rights.​

• Active Liquor Licenses Held by Both Existing Tenants.​

 

Significant Upside Through Lease-Up of Developable Pads:

• ±68,000 Square ft.​ Outparcel Provides New Ownership With the Flexibility to Accommodate either a Single or Dual Drive-Thru Configuration.​

• Developable Outparcel was Formerly a Sit-Down Restaurant With Existing Utilities to the Site.​

• Developable Outparcel has Three (3) Existing Curb-Cuts that Exclusively Cater to the Pad(s).​

 

Infill Neighborhood Site Within Densely Populated Community:

• Site Located in an Opportunity Zone and a Transit Overlay District Zone.​

• First Neighborhood Shopping Center Upon Exiting the 215-Freeway and Heading East along Base Line Street.​

• Desirable Site Accessibility Resulting from Four (4) Curb Cuts on Base Line Street, Two (2) Curb Cuts on Arrowhead Avenue, One (1) Curb Cut on D Street and Exclusive Loading Area from 13th Street.​

• Close Proximity to 322 Affordable Housing Units Recently Developed by Institutional Developer (National CORE).​

• CG-1 Zoning Permits the Construction of 266 or More Units for Senior Citizen and Senior Congregate Care Housing.​

 

Location Advantages – Limited Competition:

• Positioned Within the City and County of San Bernardino, the Shopping Center Serves as an Essential Neighborhood Hub.​

• The Property’s Strategic Location at the Bustling Intersection of North Base Line Street and North Arrowhead Avenue Yields High Traffic, With over 38,000 Cars Per Day.​

 

City and Growth Factors:

• The City of San Bernardino Stands as a Beacon of Steady Population and Job Growth.​

• Over the Past Three Years, the Addition of 316,000 Jobs is Attributed to the City’s Emphasis on Education, Retail, and Distribution Sectors.​

• The Property Enjoys Close Proximity, a Mere Three Miles, to the San Bernardino International Airport (SBD), which Boasts Remarkable Cargo Capabilities.​ Notably, a $200 Million Redevelopment Project has been Approved, Solidifying the Airport’s Status as a Robust Air Cargo Distribution Center, With Giants like Amazon as Stakeholders.​

 

Market Drivers & Demographics:

• Strategic Placement Between Two Significant College Campuses Enhances the Property’s Appeal: Located 4.5 Miles South of California State University San Bernardino (CSUSB) and 2.5 Miles North of San Bernardino Valley College.​

• A Densely Populated Area Within a Three Mile Radius Encompasses Around 156,000 Individuals, With an Average Household Income of $55,358.​ Moreover, the Average Household Retail Expenditure Reaches $99,340, Reflecting Strong Consumer Purchasing Power.​

• Recently the City of San Bernardino Agreed to Update their Housing Plan to Meet their State-Mandated Goals, which Include 8,123 Additional Housing Units by 2029.​

Horvath & Tremblay is pleased to present the exclusive opportunity to acquire the Big Lots Center located at 400 Main Street in Dennisport, Massachusetts (the “Property”).​ The center is anchored by Big Lots and contains 40,055 square feet on a 4.76-acre parcel.​ The Property was originally constructed in 1975 and was renovated and repositioned in 2020 for Big Lots.​ The center is anchored by Big Lots which occupies 36,000 square feet and has 7+ years remaining on their lease with three (3), 5-year renewal options.​ Their lease also calls for attractive scheduled rent increases.​ The center also contains a 4,055 square foot vacant unit that offers significant upside through the lease up of the space.​

The Property is well located along Main Street (MA Route 28), Cape Cod’s primary commercial and commuter corridor, and benefits from outstanding visibility and frontage.​ The location is part of the dominant trade area centered along MA Route 28 near the border of Dennis and Harwich with numerous hotels and motels, businesses, national and local retailers, restaurants, and proximity to Cape Cod’s southern beaches and harbors, all of which draw significant traffic to the area.​
column4:
LEASE TERM: Big Lots signed a new 10-year lease in 2020 and they have 7+ years remaining on their corporate lease with three (3), 5-year renewal options.

ATTRACTIVE RENT INCREASES: The Big Lots lease calls for attractive $1.00 per square foot increases in rent increase every 5 years throughout the base term and at the start of each renewal option period providing the investor with an attractive increase in revenue and hedge against inflation.

STRONG CORPORATE TENANT: The Property features a corporate guarantee with Big Lots, one of the most sought-after discount retailers in the country. Big Lots, Inc. is a community retailer operating more than 1,400 Big Lots stores in 47 states, they are traded on the New York Stock Exchange under the symbol BIG.

UPSIDE POTENTIAL: The Property features a vacant end-cap unit consisting of 4,055 square feet. The opportunity exists to significantly increase the revenue at the Property through the lease up of the vacant space. The center offers outstanding visibility, frontage, and parking and has a national anchor, further increasing the desirability of the space in the leasing market.

MINIMAL LANDLORD RESPONSIBILITIES: Big Lots has a net lease and reimburses their pro-rata share real estate taxes and insurance. They also pay a fixed Common Area Maintenance fee that increases by 3% annually. The current Common Area Maintenance fee is $72,565.56 ($2.02 per square foot) which exceeds the annual common area maintenance changes.

PRIME RETAIL LOCATION: The Property is well located along Main Street (MA Route 28) and benefits from outstanding visibility and frontage. The Property is 1-mile from MA Route 134, the area’s primary north south corridor which provides direct access to US Route 6 and the shores of the Cape Cod Bay. The Big Lots Center is part of the trade area centered along MA Route 28 near the border of Dennis and Harwich with numerous hotels and motels, businesses, national and local retailers, restaurants, and proximity to Cape Cod’s southern beaches and harbors, all of which draw significant traffic to the area.

ECONOMIC DRIVERS: Dennisport’s economy is closely tied to its status as a popular tourist destination on Cape Cod. Dennisport benefits from a diverse range of businesses and services that cater to both residents and the influx of seasonal tourists who flock to the area during the summer months. Tourism is the backbone of Dennisport's economy. The village's proximity to beautiful Nantucket Sound beaches, such as Sea View Beach, Glendon Road Beach, and Haigis Beach, makes it a sought-after destination for vacationers. A significant portion of the local economy relies on tourism-related businesses. Dennisport's Main Street is lined with charming boutiques, gift shops, and galleries that draw people to the area. These establishments cater to both tourists and local residents. The summer season is especially lucrative for these businesses, as vacationers explore the village and shop for souvenirs and unique items.

TRAFFIC COUNTS: On average more than 12,300 vehicles pass the Property daily along Main Street (MA Route 28). The traffic counts during the summer months (peak season) often double or triple.

DEMOGRAPHICS: Approximately 38,200 people live within 5-miles of the Property with an average household income of $105,970. More than 93,100 people live within 5-miles of the Property with an average household income of $116,361. Additionally, the population in the area swells to more than triple in the summer months as vacationers from the Greater Boston Area and throughout the northeast descend on Cape Cod.

Marcus & Millichap is pleased to present for your acquisition review South Western Plaza in Marion, Indiana.​

The South Western Plaza is a 7,140 square foot shopping center located at 3409 S.​ Western Ave, directly across from Tractor Supply Company, sandwiched between Walmart to the North and Meijer to the South.​ The strip benefits from the 24,007 vehicles that drive by each day.​ Owners can expect that traffic for years to come as the VA’s Northern Indiana Hospital is 3 miles away.​ 2 miles to the South opens up to Indiana Wesleyan University’s 345 acre campus, home to more than 3,165 students on site.​ Marion and the surrounding area are well diversified with employers which include IWU, Ball State (22,000 students), Marion Hospital, VA Northern Indiana Hospital, and General Motors.​ In 2022, GM announced a $491 million investment to expand the Marion Metal Stamping Plant that already employees 750 people.​ Driving the market will show the Shoppes are located on the path of progress.​

Investors can enjoy a predictable, passive income with the NNN leases already in place requiring minimal landlord responsibility.​ The positive economic outlook for Marion, along with the high traffic counts should increase the probability of tenants’ long-term commitment to the complex on top of their already low rents.​ The tenant lineup and massive upside from the 47.5% vacancy make the South Western Plaza a perfect investment opportunity for owners looking for the rare strip center with genuine upside.​

Atlantic Capital Partners has been exclusively engaged to market for sale Braintree Marketplace, a grocery-anchored shopping center that serves as the dominant component of the condominium association that governs this super-regional power center ideally positioned in Braintree, Massachusetts.​ The asset, leased to Nordstrom Rack, Ulta and a national grocery operator, is one of the most desirable shopping centers in Metro Boston given the exceptional access, visibility and co-tenancy.​

The 9 AC site is ideally positioned just off Route 3, which sees 106,018 vehicles per day and is the sole highway that services the affluent communities located south of downtown Boston.​ As the most prominent power center in one of the strongest retail markets in Greater Boston, the asset serves a regional trade area which includes a population of over 240,000 people within a 5 mile radius.​

The institutional offering is being marketed free-and-clear of existing debt without a formal asking price via a call for offers process.​

column2: New Offering | 30K SF Dollar Tree Anchored Center in Cleveland, TN
column3:
SRS Investment Properties Group, as exclusive broker, is pleased to present the opportunity to acquire Candies Creek – a 30,196± SF neighborhood center, anchored by a brand new Dollar Tree and located in Cleveland, TN.​

Anchored by Dollar Tree with a 10-Year Lease

Candies Creek is anchored by a brand-new Dollar Tree with term through 2034.​ Occupying 15,674± SF, Dollar Tree provides an incoming buyer with a strong, expanding national anchor on which to build in executing the lease-up of the remaining 3,750± SF of available space.​

 

Major Road Expansion: TN-60

Well-positioned at the signalized intersection of Paul Huff Pkwy and TN-60 – two of Cleveland’s primary traffic thoroughfares - Candies Creek accesses 31,965 VPD in front of the Property.​ Bolstering consumer accessibility, TN-60 is currently undergoing a $54M project to expand the road from two to five lanes, including a new Candies Creek bridge, a dedicated center turn lane, expanded shoulders and sidewalks, and upgraded street lighting.​ Significant synergistic retail development along the expansion and adjacent to the Property includes Fast Pace Health Urgent Care, Creekside Veterinary Clinic, and McDonald’s, along with existing outparcels – Walgreen’s and O’Reilly’s.​

 

Cleveland, TN 

Candies Creek Shopping Center is located in Cleveland, TN – the county seat and largest city within Bradley County.​ A principal component of the Chattanooga-Cleveland-Dalton, TN-GA CSA, Cleveland lies roughly 30 miles northeast of Downtown Chattanooga and 80 miles southwest of Knoxville.​ Home to the Cherokee National Forest as well as the Ocoee and Hiwasee Rivers, the area boasts excellent whitewater rafting which draws visitors to the area almost year-round for outdoor recreation.​ With 13 Fortune 500 manufacturing facilities, Cleveland boasts the fifth-largest industrial economy in Tennessee.​ Major companies include Whirlpool, Duracell, Amazon, Coca-Cola, International Paper, Rock-Tenn, Rubbermaid and more.​ Cleveland also serves as the corporate headquarters for Life Care Centers of America: the largest privately held nursing facility company in the United States.​
column4:
Well-located on the north side of Cleveland, TN at the highly trafficked, signalized intersection of Paul Huff Pkwy and Georgetown Rd NW (TN-60), accessing 31,965 VPD

Anchored by a brand new 15,674± SF Dollar Tree with a 10-year lease through April of 2034

Shops comprised of almost entirely e-commerce proof, service-oriented retail uses - Including food, financial services, and medical providers

Surrounded by beneficial national outparcel draws – O’Reilly Auto Parts and Walgreen’s - Along with newly developed Fast Pace Health Urgent Care, Creekside Veterinary Hospital and McDonald’s, directly across the street

Strong trade area demographics characterized by a growing population, with an Avg. HH Income of $90,000 within three miles of the Property

Opportunity to continue to add value to the Property via the lease-up of 12.42% of the Total GLA

$54M expansion of TN-60 underway in front of the Property, including 5-lane expansion - New Candies Creek bridge, center turn lane and improved shoulders, sidewalks and lighting

column3:
Carthage Marketplace (the “Property”), is a Burkes Outlet anchored retail neighborhood shopping center totaling 45,000 SF.​ The Center is shadow anchored to an HEB Grocery anchored center and is conveniently located in Carthage, TX.​ The property is currently 90% occupied and offers the ability to increase net operating income through in-place rental increases and the future development of an existing in-line pad site next to Dollar Tree.​

Carthage Marketplace is a single-story retail neighborhood center situated on 5.96 acres at the SW corner of Loop Road and US Hwy 79, just 2.3 miles West of downtown Carthage.​ The Center is located on the main retail corridor in the area with over 17,000 VPD passing the center.​ The property has three points of ingress/ egress at a lighted intersection and is easily visible in all directions.​ Carthage's economy has historically been tied to the oil and gas industry.​ The city is in the East Texas oil field, which has contributed significantly to its economic development.​ The city's economic drivers also include agriculture, healthcare, education, and retail.​

Carthage Marketplace’s tenant mix includes a diverse variety of national and local retailers.​ The property is anchored by Burkes Outlet with who’s base lease term extends through 2032 and features 5 remaining options going through 2052.​ Additional tenants include Shoe Sensation with a base term through 2030, Dollar Tree, B & B Pizza, and Prime Communication.​

Area demographics offer a population of 15,500 people within a 10-mile radius and average household incomes over $90,000.​ Carthage Marketplace offers investors the opportunity to acquire a stabilized asset in a strong and growing trade area with the ability to increase NOI through in place rental increases and the potential to develop an in-line pad site
column4:

• Burkes recently executed a 12-year lease, which takes them to the year 2032. Five additional 5-year extension options remain.

• Upside through the potential to develop an additional in-line building pad.

• Demographics of over 15,500 people and an average household income of $90,000 within a ten-mile radius.

• Carthage is well situated at the interchange of Loop Road and US 78, just off of Interstate 436. With a combined 17,000 vehicles per day in front of the Center the property has both great local and regional access.

• Stable cash flow with strong historical leasing and tenants.

column3:
Marcus & Millichap has been selected to exclusively market for sale, Centre Shops of Longboat Key, a prestigious shopping center strategically positioned in Manatee County within the flourishing North Port-Sarasota-Bradenton Metropolitan Area of Florida.​ This meticulously designed property, originally constructed in 1986 and thoughtfully revitalized in 2015, offers a generous 37,880 square feet of premium retail space.​ It commands a prime location along the esteemed Gulf of Mexico Drive, placing it mere steps away from the pristine white sand beaches that draw residents and visitors alike.​

What truly sets this opportunity apart is the enduring prosperity of its tenants.​ A significant number of businesses at this location have thrived for over a decade, attesting to their solid track record of successful operations.​ Nestled in a charming beachside community known for its affluent residents and consistent vacation rentals, Centre Shops of Longboat Key comprises five buildings, collectively boasting substantial frontage along the highly coveted Gulf of Mexico Drive.​ Currently, the property enjoys an impressive 95% occupancy rate, primarily due to the presence of long-term tenants, ensuring new ownership a dependable and steady cash flow.​

Under the current ownership’s attentive stewardship, significant enhancements have been made to all structures, including the installation of new roofs, a revamped parking lot, and upgraded exterior lighting.​ These improvements not only reflect a commitment to excellence but also ensure the shopping center’s ease of maintenance for its future owner.​ In summary, Centre Shops of Longboat Key presents an extraordinary investment opportunity, with its strategic location, impressive tenant history, and recent property improvements promising long-term stability and potential for investors.​

Horvath & Tremblay is pleased to present the exclusive opportunity to acquire the new construction two-tenant plaza located at 1549 White Mountain Highway in North Conway, New Hampshire (the “Property”).​ The build to suit, two-tenant plaza is improved with Chipotle and Aspen Dental and contains 6,197 square feet on a 1.61-acre parcel.​ The Property was completed in 2021, Chipotle has 7+ years remaining on their lease with four (4), 5-Year renewal options.​ Aspen Dental signed a new 10-year lease with three (3), 5-year renewal options.​ Aspen Dental’s space is under construction, and the seller will escrow their rent from closing until their rent commencement date.​ Both tenants’ leases call for attractive rent increases every 5-years throughout their primary lease terms and at the start of their renewal options.​

The Property is situated in one of the best locations in North Conway to capture passing motorists on the heavily-travelled US Route 302/NH Route 16 commercial corridor (White Mountain Highway) which includes most of the area’s retail, dining, lodging and entertainment options.​ The Property is also located adjacent to the entrance for Settler’s Green, a popular 75-store, 500,000 square foot shopping center which helps drive considerable traffic to the area.​
column4:
NEW CONSTRUCTION: The Build-to-Suit Property was completed in 2021. Chipotle has 7+ years remaining on their lease with four (4), 5-year renewal options. Aspen Dental signed a new 10-year lease with three (3), 5-year renewal options. Aspen Dental’s space is under construction. Chipotle benefits from a modern design with outdoor seating and a Chipotlane (drive-thru).

ATTRACTIVE RENT INCREASES: The Chipotle lease calls for a 10% rent increase every 5 years throughout the base term and at the start of each option period and the Aspen Dental lease calls for a 10% increase in year 6 and 8% increases at the start of each renewal option providing the investor with an attractive increase in revenue and hedge against inflation.

MINIMAL LANDLORD RESPONSIBILITIES: Both Chipotle and Aspen Dental have net leases with minimal Landlord responsibilities. The tenants reimburse their pro-rata share of all operating expenses, repairs, and maintenance of the property, making it an attractive investment for the passive real estate investor.

DYNAMIC CORPORATE TENANTS: The Property features a corporate guarantee with Chipotle, one of the most sought-after restaurant brands in the country. Total revenue for 2021 was $7.54 billion, an increase of 26.11% from 2020. Chipotle opened 215 new restaurants during 2021 bringing the total restaurant count at year-end to 2,966. Chipotle planned to open an additional 225-250 locations in 2022, 80% of which are expected to included a Chipotlane. The Aspen Dental network includes 900 offices, in 43 states, owned and operated by independent practice owners and dentists, who operate with clinical autonomy and share a commitment to creating access to care for those who need it most. These independent practice owners recorded more than five million patient visits in 2021, driven by a commitment to breaking down barriers to quality, affordable oral health care.

CHIPOTLANE: Digital sales remain a major bright spot for the chain, growing 202.5% year over year to $776.4 million. Digital orders now make up 48.8% of sales, with about half of those orders for delivery and the rest for order-ahead transactions, such as instore pickup and Chipotlane drive-thrus. The drive-thrus (Chipotlanes) are significant for the chain, generating about 10% more in sales than those locations without them.

PRIME RETAIL LOCATION: The Property is situated in one of the best locations in North Conway to capture passing motorists on the heavilytravelled US Route 302/NH Route 16 commercial corridor (White Mountain Highway) which includes most of the area’s retail, dining, lodging and entertainment options. The Property is also located adjacent to the entrance for Settler’s Green, a popular 75-store, 500,000 square foot shopping center which helps drive considerable traffic to the area.

RECESSION & E-COMMERCE RESISTANT TENANT: With an Aging babyboomer population, and strong area demographics, the need for brick and mortar medical and dental office buildings will continue to increase. This industry is unaffected by recessions and the need for personal interaction and specific medical aids can not be satisfied through e-commerce.

RETAIL TRADE AREA: Digital sales remain a major bright spot for the chain, growing 202.5% year over year to $776.4 million. Digital orders now make up 48.8% of sales, with about half of those orders for delivery and the rest for order-ahead transactions, such as in-store pickup and Chipotlane drive-thrus. The drive-thrus (Chipotlanes) are significant for the chain, generating about 10% more in sales than those locations without them.

TRAFFIC COUNTS: More than 16,800 vehicles pass the Property daily along White Mountain Highway (US Route 302/NH Route 16).

DEMOGRAPHICS: Approximately 10,500 people live within 5-miles of the Property with an average household income of $89,393. More than 20,300 people live within 10-miles of the Property with an average household income of $90,649.

This property is listed in conjunction with Texas-licensed real estate broker Delta Commercial.​

column3:
Cornerstone Village is a 100% occupied, three tenant - 9,101 square foot retail strip center located in the growing Atlanta suburb of Dacula, Georgia.​ The tenant roster features an e-commerce resistant mix of Friends Bar & Grill, Creations Barbershop, and Avanti Nail Spa.​ The property was built in 2007 with all brick construction and shows zero visible deferred maintenance.​ The local sub-market for retail shows very little vacancy with rents averaging about $24 per square foot range contrasted to the subject property with an average base rent of only $17.93 per square foot.​ The property is positioned adjacent to Dacula Village, a Publix anchored retail center and features direct visibility on Dacula Road with traffic counts approximately 17,300 +/- vehicles per day.​

The area surrounding the property has excellent demographics with an average household income of $117,451 in a one mile radius.​ There has been significant growth in the area with the five mile population up 230% since 2000, and projected to grow another 8% in the next five years.​ There are many new residential and retail developments nearby showing this continued growth in the area.​ It is directly across from Hebron Christian Academy which has over 1,150 students, and in 2019 underwent a $10M Expansion project with a State of the Art Middle School and Fine Arts Center.​

column2: Value Add Opportunity | 8.64% CAP Rate | 10.52% Potential CAP Rate by Year 3
column3:
Marcus & Millichap is pleased to exclusively list Crowder Center, a 31,552-square-foot shopping center located at 5790 Crowder Boulevard in New Orleans, Louisiana.​ The property is situated on the corner of Interstate 10 (113,600 vehicles per day) and Crowder Boulevard (16,400 vehicles per day) in East New Orleans.​

Producing a day one CAP rate of 8.64 percent, Crowder Center presents an investor with a rare opportunity to acquire a stabilized asset well above the current national average CAP rate of 6.71 percent for retail properties (according to data provided by CoStar).​ Crowder Center is 93.64 percent occupied, and 86.66 percent of the tenants have occupied the center with ongoing tenure of 8 years or more.​

An investor can increase the Year-1 CAP rate of 8.64 percent to achieve a 10.52 percent CAP rate in Year-3 by maintaining occupancy, renewing leases at the scheduled renewal option rates, and leasing the 2,007-square-feet of vacancy at $13.00/square foot plus triple-net reimbursements.​ (The average market rent per square foot in the New Orleans East submarket is $13.74 according to data provided by CoStar).​

Another opportunity to increase returns with this property would be through refinancing once interest rates reduce to a range of 7 percent or below.​

Decatur Corners is a shopping center that is 100% occupied in Decatur, TX (DFW MSA).​ All of the leases are NNN and contain a healthy layout of strong tenants.​ The tenants at this building include World Finance, Excel Cardiac, Skyline Nails & Spa, ABA North Texas, Decatur Vapes and Double C Cinema (Pylon Sign).​ World Finance has been at the center for over 16 years which shows their committment to the center and area.​ Situated on over an acre of land, the parking lot is cement and the property was constructed in 1990 with a quality brick façade.​ Over the years, a significant amount of TI work has been done to the shopping center.​ The roof is a 2016 TPO roof with a transferable warranty until 2031.​

This property is a rare opportunity to acquire a small price point shopping center in the Dallas MSA.​ The rents are between at market to below market for the area which will allow a healthy rent growth for the tenants in the future.​ In front of the center, there is a Wendy’s that was recently renovated.​ The property is located in a high traffic area of Decatur with over 49,000 vehicles per day on Hwy 287 and over 17,000 vehicles per day on S FM 51.​ The 3 mile radius has an average household income of over $94,000 with estimates of 4.29% population growth from 2023-2028.​ Many businesses and developments are coming to the area including a mixed use development directly west of the property (2 commercial lots, 257 single family, 139 town homes).​ A future development called Decatur Crossroads is attracting more businesses and is located near the shopping center.​

column2: 8.00% CAP | 18,748 SF | Low Price Per SF
column3:
We are pleased to present the exciting opportunity to acquire a 4-unit 18,748 SF multi-tenant retail strip center located in Clarksburg, West Virginia.​ The tenant mix consists of retail-oriented tenants that conveniently serve customers in the nearby community and surrounding areas.​ Dollar General, the anchor tenant, has successfully operated this location since 2005, extending its original 15-year lease on multiple occasions therefore displaying the tenant's trust and commitment to this site.​ The Dollar General lease is corporately guaranteed by Dollar General Corporation which holds a credit rating of “BBB”, classified as Investment Grade.​ Grandma Cookie's Hot Dog Express has also been a long term, reliable tenant who has continuously maintained their lease throughout the years.​ The strip center is located on one of Clarksburg's busiest intersections with nearly 21,000 vehicles per day.​ This has undoubtedly attracted the center's newest tenants, Charleston Furniture Direct and Clarksburg Nutrition, who signed brand new leases earlier this year.​

Clarksburg is a city in and the county seat of Harrison County, West Virginia, United States, in the north-central region at the intersection of Interstate 79 and U.​S.​ Route 50, the second busiest interchange in the state.​ Clarksburg was formed in 1785 in the state of Virginia.​ Clarksburg is unique in that it is the largest city in the region, yet still has the advantages of a small hometown community.​ It is the principal city of the Clarksburg, WV Micropolitan Statistical Area, which had a population of 89,718 in 2019.​ Clarksburg was named National Small City of the Year in 2011 by the National League of Cities.​ A rich mix of retail, industry, and government services, with a thriving business community exist, along with many recreational facilities and one of the best preserved historic downtowns in the state.​
column4:
100% OCCUPIED - The Center is has excellent historical occupancy and is currently occupied by Dollar General & Grandma Cookies Hot Dogs, both long term tenants, as well as Charleston Furniture Direct & Clarksburg Nutrition.

RECENT TENANT REMODEL! - In 2022, Dollar General remodeled the entire store's interior at their own cost, showing strong commitment to the site and renewal potential at the end of the current lease term.

LONG TERM ANCHOR TENANT - Dollar General has had continued presence at the center since 2005, exercising several lease extensions along the way, speaking to the tenant's strong commitment and belief in this location.

RECENT OWNER INVESTMENT - Owners recently had the parking lot re striped and installed a state of the art surveillance system in addition to hiring an on-site maintenance person.

STRONG TRAFFIC COUNTS - The immediate area sees nearly 10,500 vehicles per day from S Chestnut St. and 10,337 from S Bypass Rd. This site is located up the street from McDonald's, Walgreens and Advance Auto Parts. The strip center takes advantage of robust traffic counts from nearby local and major national tenants such as Family Dollar, Food Lion, O'Reilly Auto Parts, Burger King, Sheetz, Pizza Hut, Subway, Little Caesars, Wendy's, McDonald's, Dairy Queen, and many, many others.

SOLID DEMOGRAPHICS - Solid population counts of 5,216 within 1 mile, 24,121 within 3 miles, 31,947 within 5 miles and 58,586 within 10 miles.

Approximately a .3 acres of land.​

The opportunity sits along Military Trail just south of Donald Ross Road in the lifestyle center known as Donald Ross Village.​ The project is mixed-use and benefits from shared parking.​ Our primary interest is to ground lease or sell the pad at a fair number.​ We can assist Buyer in obtaining site plan approval as we have developed several projects in Palm Beach Gardens including Donald Ross Village and the on site Homewood Suites.​

Donald Ross Village, Abacoa Plaza (Publix anchored center to the north), and Alton Town Center (Publix, Home Depot, L.​A.​ Fitness, Pet Smart anchored center to the west) are 100% leased.​ This proposed pad would be in close proximity to CVS, Dunkin Donuts, the 20,000 sq.​ft.​ Palm Beach Sports Club (formerly Gold’s Gym), Cleveland Clinic, Resolute, Med Express, Cycle Bar, and sits along Military at one of the entrances to Donald Ross Village and at the entrance to the 153 unit Cielo townhome community.​

Non-parking intensive uses preferred.​

Cannot conflict with existing businesses at Donald Ross Village

Max building size (TBD) will likely be ~2,000-2,500 sq.​ft.​, subject to site plan approval as well as use, parking needs, and other details.​ Seller to assist buyer with site plan approval.​

Building design must be consistent with existing project’s design.​

Monument Signage available.​
