Marcus & Millichap is pleased to exclusively offer a Family Dollar anchored center with Family Dollar offering five years term remaining backed by a corporate guarantee.​ The center enjoys full occupancy and underwent renovations in 2018.​ Notably, both tenants have the added benefit of rental increases available throughout their extension options.​

This center ranks in the top 83% of Indiana Family Dollar stores, drawing an impressive 55,000 visitors within a 12-month period according to Placer.​ai.​

Strategically situated in a prime location, the center is just 0.2 miles away from Interstate 94's interchange, with 206,635 vehicles per day.​ Additionally, it enjoys proximity to the 25th Avenue and Grant Street intersection, with a daily traffic count of 25,776 vehicles.​ With over 255 feet of frontage along 25th Avenue, the center offers high visibility to passing motorists.​ Furthermore, it is conveniently located 0.7 miles from Methodist Hospitals Midlake Campus and just 3.2 miles from the recently opened Hard Rock Casino Northern Indiana, a $300 million establishment featuring 1,700 slots, 80 table games, a sportsbook, five restaurants, two bars, and a live entertainment venue.​

The center benefits from its close proximity to various retail properties, including Aldi, Fresh Country Market, Walgreens, Taco Bell, Sharks, Pizza Hut, Fresenius Medical Care, Midas, and more.​ It is also conveniently served by the 25th and Grant bus stop, where two different bus lines provide access.​

Additionally, it is just 1.9 miles away from Indiana University Northwest, with a student population of 3,600.​ The center benefits from a dense population, with 60,342 people residing within a three-mile radius.​ It is also part of the Chicago Metropolitan Statistical Area (MSA), situated 33.4 miles southeast of Chicago, further enhancing its regional significance and accessibility.​

column3:
For 57 years, its customers included actor Paul Newman, race car driver Kyle Petty, industry titans, I-94 travelers between Detroit and Chicago looking for a great meal, and area residents celebrating special occasions.​  Gilbert’s Steakhouse has been a landmark in Mid-Michigan for three generations.​  The historic restaurant was known for its many “Tiffany” style lamps & other antiques situated throughout the restaurant, banquet hall and bar.​  There is a fireplace in the lobby, and another in “The Cabin Bar,” which was originally a log home.​  The building has been expanded several times to the state-of-the-art structure that exists today.​  It truly has “one of a kind” ambiance.​

 

In 2004, newspaper headlines in Jackson blared “End of an Era” to describe how locals felt about the closing of this “area” institution.​  Patrons waited in 2 hour lines to hug the owner goodbye & wish him well.​  The current owner has since invested more than $1,250,000 in renovating the property, including new roof, gutters, electrical system, HVAC, kitchen equipment, tables and chairs, mahogany paneling, granite bar tops, carpet, restrooms, etc.​  The entire property was gutted and rebuilt to today’s standards, but it maintains the elegant charm and ambience of the historic Gilbert’s.​

 

Current Condition:

The building has been vacant for several years, during which time a truck hit the port cochere and damaged the corner of it.​  There was a storm in the summer of 2021 that caused some leaks in the roof; they are currently being repaired.​  Some of the restaurant equipment has been sold.​  Most of the antiques and Tiffany lamps have been sold.​  The restaurant is still fundamentally sound and beautiful and ready to be “recreated” into a new concept.​
column4: The restaurant is surrounded by five nationally branded hotels, none of which have kitchen facilities or meeting rooms. Not only is there tremendous opportunity for catering and banquets, but the hotels provide nearly 1,000 guests on a daily basis that are looking for a good place to eat. This is truly an extraordinary and unique opportunity.

The Uptown Scottsbluff area has numerous retailers nearby including Walmart Supercenter, Target, The Home Depot, Menard’s, Hobby Lobby, Walgreens, McDonald’s, Culver’s, Taco Bell, KFC, Harbor Freight, AutoZone, and more.​ Directly neighboring the subject property, Uptown Scottsbluff (formerly Monument Mall) is currently undergoing a revitalization which is expected to significantly increase traffic and encourage cross shopping synergies.​ Additionally, several schools surround the property including Western Nebraska Community College, Scottsbluff Senior High School, and Bluffs Middle School which have a combined enrollment surpassing 4,200 students.​

This is a great value add opportunity for investors or developers seeking a prominent location in Scottsbluff, NE with excellent potential.​

column3: Sean Glickman, CCIM, managing director at Cushman and Wakefield and Chris Smith, director of capital markets are proud to offer for sale Fort Caroline Trading Post, a SF center featuring a great mix of national and local grocery, gym, restaurant and services tenants.​ This offering is in a premier location in the Jacksonville market and contains nationally recognized tenants like Winn-Dixie, Planet Fitness and Citi Trends.​
column4:
• Strong tenant lineup with national tenants Winn-Dixie, Planet Fitness and Citi Trends.

• Long history of success at the property with Winn-Dixie since 1984, Great Wall Chinese Restaurant since 2001, Best Nails of Jax since 2003, and Citi Trends since 2006.

• All national tenants have multiple option periods that extend their leases well into the future.

• Value-add potential with multiple tenants significantly below market.

• Based on the expected cap rate, the price per SF is well below replacement cost.

• Dense local population in the 5-minute drive time with HH income of $69,747

• Aldi acquiring Winn-Dixie adds credibility and potential value add, as Aldi may shrink the store and give back more inline space.

• Winn-Dixie store sales are decent and in an uptrend, currently at $308 per square foot.

• The health ratio of Winn-Dixie is 2.9%. This is a store they will keep open for a long time.

• Aldi may also decide to close the store. This will offer a significant value add potential as a new anchor will pay much higher rent that is currently paid by WD ($6.4/SF with limited CAM).

column2: 8% Cap | Home Depot & Schnucks Shadow Anchored | St. Louis MSA
column3:
Marcus & Millichap, as exclusive advisor, is pleased to present the opportunity to acquire 100% fee simple interest in Gannon Plaza II, (“The Property”), an 18,519 square foot “Medtail” strip center located in Festus, MO (St.​ Louis MSA).​ The Property is shadow anchored by the nation’s leading home improvement retailer (Home Depot) and St Louis’s market dominant grocer (Schnucks).​

Built in 2006, the Property is 100% leased and has a long-standing track record of maintaining high occupancy levels, 83% of the Year-1 Revenue is tied to leases that commenced more than 17 years ago and is composed entirely of medical (83%) and service (17%) based, e-commerce resistant retail uses.​ The Property’s anchor tenant, Twin Cities Surgery Center, is an original tenant having renewed and expanded several times with significant capital invested into their space demonstrating a long-term commitment to the Property and creating an extremely sticky tenant base.​ Twin Cities Surgery Center is an affiliate of United Surgical Partners International, the largest ambulatory network and surgery platform in the United States with more than 475 locations.​ The Property’s primarily medical based tenant lineup also features Nikodem Dental Group, another original tenant, and recently welcomed its newest tenant, The Joint Chiropractor, who signed a brand new 5-year lease in 2022, marking only the third time a suite has turned over since its construction in 2004.​

Gannon Plaza II is located immediately off I nterstate-55 near the intersection of Veterans Blvd, the trade area’s main arterial thoroughfare with impressive daily traffic counts of over 86,000 VPD.​ The Property benefits from its location within the respective trade areas preeminent shopping center in a market with limited supply and high barriers to entry.​ Anchored by two category leading necessity-based retailers; Home Depot and Schnucks Supermarket, the Property is within one of the most highly trafficked shopping centers in the market.​ Other nearby national retailers include Walmart Supercenter, Aldi, Lowe’s Home Improvement, Panera Bread, Starbuck’s, McDonald’s, and Bank of America, among others.​

The Property is being offered free and clear of debt at a 8.0% cap rate totaling $5,585,000.​
column4:
SURGERY CENTER ANCHORED STRIP CENTER

  • ​

    Anchored By Twin Cities Surgery Center, An Original Tenant With Nearly 20-Years Of Operating History At The Property That’s Expanded Their Space, Exercised Multiple Lease Renewals During Their Tenure, And Invested Significant Capital Into Their Buildout. Twin Cities Surgery Center Is An Affiliate Of United Surgical Partners International, The Largest Ambulatory Network And Surgery Platform In The United States With More Than 475 Locations.

LONG STANDING TENURE  & HISTORIAL OCCUPANCY

  • ​

    83% Of The Year-1 Revenue Is Tied To Leases That Commenced More Than 17 Years Ago And Is Composed Entirely Of Medical (83%) And Service (17%) Based, E-Commerce Resistant Retail Uses. Three Of The Five Tenants Are Original Having Each Exercised Renewals Several Times Since Construction. The Weighted Average Tenant Tenure Is More Than Fifteen Years.

DOMINANT LOCATION

  • ​

    Gannon Plaza II Is Positioned Within The Market Dominant, 200,000+ Square Foot Power Shopping Center Anchored By Category Leading Retailers Home Depot And Schnucks Supermarket. Located Immediately Off Interstate-55 And Veterans Memorial Blvd with Convenient Access and High Visibility, The Property Is Perfectly Positioned At The Primary Intersection In The Trade Area With A Combined Traffic Count Of More Than 86,000 VPD.

MEDTAIL

  • ​

    “Medtail” Properties Such As Gannon Plaza Are One Of The Fastest Growing And Desirable Segments Within Commercial Real Estate. Consumers Preference Is Shifting Towards Accessible Health And Wellness Centers In Convenient Locations, And Healthcare Tenants Are Rushing To Meet Demand. Medtail Properties Offer Investors A More Stable Rent Roll With Less Turnover And Higher Rent Growth.

EXPANSIVE TRADE AREA

  • ​

    Gannon Plaza II Is A Part Of The Festus & Crystal City, Commonly Referred To As The Twin City’s Trade Area, Which Serves As Regional Hub For Retail And Health Medical Services. The Trade Area Boasts The Only Home Depot And Lowe’s Within A 15-Mile Radius And Only Walmart Within A 10-Mile Radius. It Possesses The Only Traditionally Sized Grocer, Schnucks, Within 13-Miles. The 251-Bed Regional Hospital, Mercy Hospital Jefferson, Is The Only Hospital Of Its Size And Offering Within 20 Miles To The North And Approximately 30 Miles To The South. Together The Retail And Health Medical Offerings Draw Residents From Well Beyond The Municipality’s Boundaries Creating An Expansive Vibrant Trade Area.

column3:
Prime Net Lease is pleased to present the exciting opportunity to acquire a 10,790 SF 6 unit multi-tenant retail center, known as the Gaslite Square Plaza, located in Milan, IL.​ The tenant mix consists of retail-oriented tenants that conveniently serve customers in the nearby community and surrounding areas.​ Most of the tenants have been long term, reliable and who have continuously maintained their leases throughout the years, showing their strong commitment to the area and site itself.​ The plaza is located on one of Milan's busiest intersections with nearly 17,000 vehicles per day.​ This has attracted the plaza's newest tenant, Bill's Gaming Cafe, who spent nearly $100,000 on recent renovations.​ The site shares a parking lot with Dollar General, while directly next door are both KFC and AutoZone and across the street are Hy-Vee and CVS.​ Local and major national tenants closeby include Pizza Hut, McDonald's, Hardee's, Jimmy John's, Fazoli's, Target, Ross, Hobby Lobby, Dollar General, Walgreens and many others.​

The site has quick access to US Hwy 92, I-280, I-74 & The Quad City Airport.​ Milan is home to the John Deere North American Parts Distribution Center, one of the largest warehouses in the world.​ In June of 2022, only six miles away in Davenport, Iowa, Fair Oaks Foods announced plans to construct a state-of-the-art food production facility.​ The $134 million investment includes a 150,000 square-foot facility in the Eastern Iowa Industrial Center and will create an estimated 247 new full-time jobs.​ The company plans to start operations in early 2024.​ Construction is anticipated to begin this summer on a 32-acre site near Interstate 80.​ This development is expected to have an annual economic impact of $182 million, making it the largest business attraction project in the region’s history.​

Milan is a village in Rock Island County, Illinois.​ The village is located near the Quad Cities of Illinois and Iowa.​ The area consists of the cities of Davenport and Bettendorf in Iowa and Rock Island, Moline, and East Moline in Illinois, and their suburbs in northwest Illinois and southeast Iowa.​ The Quad Cities is located at the confluence of the Rock and Mississippi rivers, approximately 140 miles (230 km) west of Chicago, and forms the largest metropolitan area along the Mississippi River between Minneapolis–Saint Paul and the St.​ Louis metropolitan area.​ The Quad Cities Metropolitan Area consists of three counties: Scott County in Iowa, and Rock Island County and Henry County in Illinois.​ The Quad City metro population is 382,268.​ The Quad Cities Metropolitan Area is also considered part of the Great Lakes Megalopolis.​

**Dollar General & Happy Joe’s not included in sale**
column4:

John Deere Parts Distribution Center is a 2.5 million SF facility, one of the largest working warehouses in Northern America. With 61 acres under roof, the building is one half of a mile wide. Built in 1973, the Milan facility has more than 100 miles of storage racks and 90 dock doors.

  • ​

The Offering provides the investor with the opportunity to acquire the 100% leased  Grizzly Peak Shopping Center:  an 8.95 acre site  with 63,311 sqft of leasable space as well as two (2) ground lease pads; upside in the form of excess land available for development, and the only available drive through permit in the community.​ The Grizzly Peak Shopping Center enjoys a hard corner location at the prime intersection within a dense and integral retail trade corridor; and has approximately 765 lineal feet of road frontage on the arterial.​ The arterial (Ashland Street / OR Hwy 66) provides proximity to the downtown core (@ 2 miles), Southern Oregon University (@ 1 mile) and the I-5 Interchange (@ ¼ mile).​

•Inherent conditions within the community of Ashland have long prohibited any change in the Urban Growth Boundary.​ Physical terrain and historic development patterns have concentrated rooftops nearest the subject center, and relegated recent commercial development to infill and redevelopment of small sites; consequently, there are few competitor sites.​

•Long term Tenants have created a balanced center that has been strongly supported by the community.​ Bi Mart is a regionally significant retailer that has occupied the site since 1979; while Shop N Kart has represented the community as a preferred local grocer for more than four decades.​

column3:
Introducing the HARBOR VILLAGE RETAIL &OFFICE CENTER in San Pedro, CA 90732, an outstanding investment opportunity located at 2302 S.​ Western Ave.​ in San Pedro, CA.​ With a total leasable area of 31,834 sq.​ ft.​, this one and two story, fully leased property offers a stable and consistent income stream for investors, while providing a terrific Value-Add investment.​ Currently at 5.92% CAP (includes new taxes).​ Rents are undervalued by 23%.​ Increased base rents bring in a pro-forma CAP of 10.2%.​ *** New 2023 property taxes are $99,254.68, of which tenants pay taxes in addition to base rent.​ Non MTM Tenants also pay CAM.​ Financials included here are for 2022.​

Home to 22 locally known tenants, including Sorrento's, Prontos, and State Farm, this center enjoys high visibility and wide accessibility, thanks to its location on both Western Avenue and 25th Street.​ Western Avenue is the dominant retail corridor and thoroughfare for both the eastern portion of Rancho Palos Verdes as well as the city of San Pedro.​ Situated near a signalized corner and visible to over 25,300 vehicles daily, it offers a prime positioning for retail success.​

Convenience is key, with major retailers nearby - Starbucks, Rock 'N Juice, Mobil gas station, Chase Bank, Ace Hardware, and Vons and Smart ‘n Final supermarkets.​ The center boasts 88 on-site parking spaces, ensuring easy access for customers.​

With its walk score of 69 and proximity to the beach, various shops, restaurants, the Trump National Golf Club, and the upcoming LA Waterfront Promenade, this property is ideally situated for success.​ The Harbor Village Retail & Office Center offers investors the chance to capitalize on the growth potential of the dynamic San Pedro market.​ Don't miss out on this exceptional opportunity.​

Price: $8,500,000 | Occupancy: 100% | CAP Rate: 5.9%.​ Pro-Forma Value Add CAP 10.2% *** Note that tenants pay all taxes.​ Taxes have recently increased as above and tenants pay those, in addition to base rent.​ Non MTM Tenants also pay CAM.​ One of the listing agents is also part owner.​ FOR VIDEO: www.​ClaraDuranReed.​com/harborvillage
column4:
VALUE ADD INVESTMENT

The Property offers an investor numerousways to obtain yield growth, including fully renovating the center, rental rate adjustments to market rent, converting gross leases to full NNN and property enhancements. 

PRICED SIGNIFICANTLY BELOW REPLACEMENT COST

The Property includes 31,834 square feet of leasable area being offered for sale at $109.95/SF.

DIVERSE, SERVICE AND DAILY NEEDS

ORIENTED TENANT MIX

The Property is 100% occupied with a mix of food, discount, service and daily needs retailers offering a hedge against e-commerce.

LOCATED ADJACENT TO MAJOR RETAILERS/BUSINESSES

Heavily trafficked area with major businesses nearby, including Starbucks, Rock ‘N Juice, and Fantastic Sam’s as anchors next door and sharing the same parking lot, but not part of the property. Adjacent Mobil gas station, and Vons supermarket. Smart and Final Supermarket, Ace Hardware and Chase Bank across the street.

STRONG, LONG TERM TENANTS

The Property has a history of being fully occupied, including during the pandemic. Stable, well known tenants, some having occupied the center since 1963, shortly after being built. 

EXCELLENT VISIBILITY AND ACCESS

Located on main thoroughfares. The Property features frontage of 282 feet on 25th St. and 217 feet on Western Ave., both heavily trafficked streets. Both are main ingress and egress streets to San Pedro and Rancho Palos Verdes. Property has two double sided pylon signs. 

SIGNALIZED HIGH TRAFFIC LOCATION

Near signalized corner. Daily traffic count of 16,247 on Western Ave. and a traffic count of 25,370 on 25th St. 

PRIME LOCATION

Located on busy streets - main thoroughfare to enter and exit the city. Accessible to nearby Rancho Palos Verdes, Trump National Golf Club, White Point Beach, Friendship and Point Fermin Parks and the San Pedro Waterfront Development in progress. One of 3 closest retail centers to the East side of Rancho Palos Verdes and Coastal San Pedro.

column3:
Horvath & Tremblay is pleased to present the exclusive opportunity to purchase the Heights Professional Medical Plaza, an investment property located at 11721- 11761 Southwest Highway in Palos Heights, Illinois (the “Property”).​ The Property is improved by a 61,638 square foot two-story building (both levels are at grade) that contains 37,638 square feet of office/professional space and 24,000 square feet of warehouse space (all on the lower level in the rear of the Property) on a 3.21-acre parcel of land.​ The Heights Professional Medical Plaza was originally constructed in 1975 and significantly renovated in 2021 and 2022, including a new roof with a 20-year warranty (contact the agent for more details).​ The Heights Professional Medical Plaza is 100% leased and is improved by a complimentary mix of local, regional, and national tenants offering products and services for the surrounding community.​

The Heights Professional Medical Plaza is situated along Southwest Highway (IL Route 7), one of the area’s primary commercial and commuter corridors.​ The property enjoys outstanding frontage, visibility, and signage and benefits from two points of access.​ The primary point of access for the plaza is positioned at a traffic light along Southwest Highway.​ The plaza also boasts a digital sign at the signalized entrance that can be seen by oncoming traffic from both directions.​ The Heights Professional Medical Plaza is surrounded by commercial and medical tenants and is well located in the northwest corner of the city.​ The Property offers convenient access to two Metra Stations, several highways and Interstate 294.​
column4:
DIVERSE TENANT MIX: Heights Professional Medical Plaza benefits from a diverse mix of local, regional, and national tenants that provide a variety of goods and services to the surrounding community.

RENTAL INCREASES & RE TAX REIMBURSEMENTS: A majority of the tenants at Heights Professional Medical Plaza have scheduled annual rent increases throughout their primary lease terms. Additionally, a Majority of the leases also call for the tenants to reimburse any increases in real estate taxes above their respective base years, providing a steady increase in income and an attractive hedge against inflation.

STRATEGIC LOCATION: Situated at a signalized intersection of Southwest Highway and 117th Street, the Heights Professional Medical Plaza is well located along one of the area’s primary commercial and commuter corridors. The Property is surrounded by commercial buildings and medical facilities and is positioned in between two Metra Stations, Palos Heights (0.6-miles away) and Palos Park (0.8-miles away). The Property is approximately 2.5 miles from US Highway 45, 3-miles from US Highway 20 and 3.5-miles from Interstate 294. The Heights Professional Medical Plaza is also less than 2.5-miles from Moraine Valley Community College and Trinity Christian College. Additionally, the area surrounding Southwest Highway is home to densely populated residential neighborhoods with a built-in customer base for the tenants occupying the plaza.

GROWING MEDICAL OFFICE PRESENCE: The Property is well positioned in the northwest corner of Palos Heights. This portion of town is quickly becoming the destination for medical facilities and tenants. The Heights Professional Medical Plaza is across the street from the High Tech Medical Park and seconds from the Southwest Highway Physician Center. The Property is also just 1-mile from Northwest Medicine Palos Hospital, a 425-bed hospital with more than 600 physicians on staff, representing 42 medical specialties. Additionally, W College Drive (just south of the Property) is home to several medical facilities.

FRONTAGE, VISIBILITY & SIGNAGE: The Heights Professional Medical Plaza enjoys outstanding frontage (approximately 585 linear feet), visibility and signage along Southwest Highway (IL Route 7). The Property has two points of access, and the primary entrance and exit are positioned at a signalized intersection. Additionally, the monument sign is positioned at the intersection and features a digital sign that can be seen from both directions by oncoming traffic.

TRAFFIC COUNTS: More than 20,600 vehicles pass the Property each day along Southwest Highway (IL Route 7).

OUTSTANDING DEMOGRAPHICS: 74,200+ people live within a 3-mile radius of the Property with an average household income of $93,170. An impressive 227,200+ people live within a 5-mile radius of the Property. Additionally, there are more than 91,900 employees within a 5-mile radius of the property.

column2: Four Tenant Asset With Drive-Thru And Highly Sought After QSR Tenants
column3:
Marcus & Millichap is pleased to present the exclusive opportunity to acquire a brand-new retail property located at 3311 W Hillsboro Blvd, Deerfield Beach, FL.​ This prime investment features a diverse and high-profile tenant lineup, including Chipotle, Panda Express, Jersey Mike's Subs, and a dental office, offering a strong and stable cash flow for potential investors.​

Situated on a prominent corner of West Hillsboro Boulevard, the property boasts excellent visibility and benefits from high traffic counts in the thriving Deerfield Beach market.​ This newly constructed, state-of-the-art retail center is a total of 7,484 rentable square feet and is situated on an oversized 1.2-acre parcel of land.​ Each tenant is secured under long-term landlord friendly leases, with escalations, and brings a reliable income stream to the property with strong residual value.​ The retail center benefits from its strategic positioning, with proximity to residential neighborhoods, schools, recreational facilities, and is right in the middle of the neighborhood’s concentrated retail corridor.​

Deerfield Beach, part of the Miami metropolitan area, is known for its attractive beaches, lively atmosphere, and strong economic growth.​ The city's thriving retail and commercial sectors have attracted businesses and investors alike, making it an ideal location for capital appreciation.​ The influx of both residents and tourists in the area, driven by the city's well-developed amenities and vibrant community, guarantees a high level of footfall and patronage to the retail center.​

This investment presents a unique opportunity for investors to own a high-quality asset in one of Florida's rapidly growing markets with a newly constructed facility that includes a Drive-Thru, 15-Year Primary Lease Terms on its anchor tenants, and favorable location in the heart of Deerfield Beach.​

SRS Investment Properties Group, as exclusive broker, is pleased to offer the opportunity to acquire Hurricane Creek, a 62,590± SF neighborhood center, grocery-anchored by Publix, located on the southeast side of Chattanooga, TN.​ 

Chattanooga, TN-GA MSA 

Situated just southeast of the downtown Chattanooga area and Interstate 75, Hurricane Creek fronts the E Brainerd Rd retail corridor - a high growth area of the city with notable newer retail development.​ Having experienced a renaissance over the last 10 years, which has fueled its explosive growth; Chattanooga offers residents an extremely high quality of life with a bustling downtown, beautiful riverfront, majestic mountain views and some of the best outdoor recreation in the country.​ In addition to an attractive cost of living 5% below the national average, Chattanooga has some of the fastest internet in the Western Hemisphere, supporting the 3rd fastest-growing job market in the country over the last several years.​ 

Anchored by a proven neighborhood Publix - Providing a highly coveted necessity-based shopping anchor and THE #1 most desired grocer in the Southeast 

Situated in the East Brainerd corridor of Chattanooga - A rapidly growing market, which offers abundant outdoor recreation and a revitalized downtown area full of restaurants, shopping and tourist draws 

With tenure at the Property dating to 2007, Publix boasts a solid foothold in the community, supported by strong reported sales in 2022 - up an average of 13.75% YOY since 2019 

Highly affluent and growing community - Highlighted by an Avg.​ HH Income of $118,192 within one mile of the Property 

Attractive 72% anchor-to-shop space ratio, creating notable stability for passive investors seeking a more hands-off ownership scenario 

Tenant roster is comprised of 77% national retailers, further highlighted by a blend of e-commerce resistant shops, including medical, restaurant, and beauty service providers 

Well-positioned at the signalized intersection of busy East Brainerd Rd (TN-320) and Hurricane Creek Rd -Accessing 28,085 VPD in front of the Property
column4:
Anchored by the #1 Grocer in the Southeast 

With tenure at the Property since 2007, Publix at Hurricane Creek boasts an established community consumer base highlighted by strong, growing sales, which have been trending up since before COVID. A neighborhood mainstay, the store reports excellent sales, averaging a tremendous 13.75% YOY growth since 2019. 

77% National Credit Tenants  

Bolstered by Publix, Hurricane Creek is comprised of roughly 77% national credit tenants, including Domino’s Pizza, Great Clips and Benchmark Physical Therapy. Further, the entirety of the existing tenant roster consists of advantageous, e-commerce proof retail uses, counting two medical service providers, food, beverage and salon services.  

 

Fundamental Retail Strength 

With an enviable location at the signalized intersection of E Brainerd Rd (TN-320)  and Hurricane Creek Rd, the Property benefits from excellent fundamentals, which not only position the center for long-term success, but also create an appealing low-maintenance ownership scenario. Part of a growing Chattanooga sub-market, Hurricane Creek accesses 28,085 VPD along with an affluent, local consumer base with ample disposable income. A highly attractive 72% anchor-to-shop space ratio further fortifies the asset’s stability while also mitigating the leasing and management requirement, creating an excellent opportunity for passive investors.

Jones Lang LaSalle Americas, Inc.​ (“JLL”), is pleased to exclusively offer for sale the fee-simple interest in Icehouse Plaza (the “Property”) located at 2522-2550 Nicollet Ave in Minneapolis, MN.​ The 37,884 SF retail/residential mixed use asset is 100% leased and has a WALT on the commercial portion of 6.9 years.​ Featuring seven commercial and 13 residential tenants, this asset offers the unique opportunity to acquire a fully occupied, mixed-use property on the best corner in one of Minneapolis' most sought after submarkets.​

At list price, the building is well-below replacement cost on a per square foot basis.​ Additionally, over $500k in structural improvements, a roof replacement with warranties, and various common area improvements have been recently completed.​ These recent upgrades, along with strong leasing momentum, evidenced by Starbucks' recent 10 year deal in the center, illustrate the asset's ideal positioning to deliver stable cash flows for years to come.​

The property features iconic Minneapolis restaurants in the heart of Eat Street, a historic submarket with excellent fundamentals.​ The two largest tenants, Icehouse and Vertical Endeavors, which take up over half of the commercial space, have been at the property for over 11 years.​ Additionally, the property benefits from being in a high-density area central to essential amenities; within a three-mile radius, the area has a population of over 262,000 people, and the property is located between the downtown Minneapolis and the Minneapolis-Saint Paul International Airport, being just 10 minutes from both.​

column2: High Performing Kroger Anchored Center | Value-Add | Minimal Nearby Full Line Grocery Competition
column3:
CBRE is pleased to present, as the exclusive advisor, the opportunity to acquire King City Square, a Kroger-anchored neighborhood grocery center in Mount Vernon, Illinois, located 75 miles east of downtown St.​ Louis.​

King City Square is anchored by a dominant Kroger store with a fuel center (Fuel Center is NAP) that did over $42 million in 2022 sales, a 1.5% increase over 2021, and 24% over pre-COVID 2019.​ King City Square has a host of complimentary retailers to Kroger in fashion and beauty, apparel, pet supplies, and food and beverage.​ The shopping center is 93.2% occupied and features 6,415 square feet of vacant space available for lease-up.​

With its strategic location along Broadway Street, the main retail thoroughfare in Mount Vernon, King City Square benefits from its proximity to national retailers such as Dunham’s Sports, Big Lots, Ross Dress for Less, Walmart Supercenter, Kohl’s, Aldi, and Lowe’s.​ In addition, King City Square is a half mile east of Interstate 57 and Interstate 64, providing strong regional access to the shopping center.​

King City Square presents a tremendous opportunity for a future owner to acquire a top-performing Kroger anchored center with a strong value-add opportunity through the lease-up of the vacant suites.​
column4:
• ​

    Anchored by Dominant Kroger Grocer: Kroger at King City Square is the dominant grocer in the market, with January 2023 T-12 sales of almost $43 million. Sales increased by 24% over pre-COVID 2019 figures. Kroger ranks in the top 25% of Kroger stores in Illinois in foot traffic rankings according to the Placer.ai.

  • ​

    Lack of Grocery Competition: There is a true lack of grocery competition in the market, with only Walmart and Aldi providing alternative options for grocery shopping. This is the only Kroger location within a 25-mile radius, and there are no full-service grocers within this same radius.

  • ​

    Value-Add Opportunity: There are two suites totaling 6,415 square feet available for lease-up. If these suites are leased at market rental rates, a future owner can increase in place NOI by approximately 17%.

  • ​

    Recent Leasing Momentum: King City Square has experienced strong leasing momentum with the recent renewals from VIP Nails, and Asian Buffet, and the new LOI with 101 Tobacco Shop. The leasing momentum demonstrates the desirability of King City Square and the tenants’ long-term commitment to the property.

  • ​

    Complimentary Retailers: King City Square features a complimentary tenant mix with retail categories in fashion and beauty, apparel, pet supplies, and food and beverage. There are 1.3 million annual visits to the shopping center, according to Placer.ai, of which the shops generate 455,000 visits or 35% of the annual traffic.

  • ​

    Strategic Location Along Broadway Street Retail Corridor: King City Square is located along Broadway Street, the main retail corridor in Mount Vernon, Illinois. Adjacent to the shopping center is Times Square Mall, home to national retailers like Dunham’s Sports, Big Lots, Bath & Body Works, and Ross Dress for Less. Other prominent national retailers along the corridor include Walmart Supercenter, Kohls, Aldi, and Lowe’s.

  • ​

    Regional Access and High Traffic Counts: King City Square is located on Broadway and 42nd Streets with over 27,000 VPD. Broadway Street is the main east-west retail thoroughfare. A half mile east is Interstate 57, which runs north to Chicago, and Interstate 64, which connects St. Louis and Louisville. As a result of this strong regional location, there are over 1,100 hotel rooms in the immediate area.

The subject property is a freestanding Kohl’s department store located in Westland (Detroit MSA), MI.​ There are over 13 years remaining on an absolute NNN ground lease which includes structured rental increases every 5-Years in the (4) five-year option periods.​ The lease is corporately guaranteed by Kohl’s (NYSE: KSS), one the largest national retailers with over 1,160 locations in 49 states.​ According to PlacerAI, this is the second busiest Kohl’s in the state of Michigan.​

The property is strategically located in a dense retail trade area with major national tenants surrounding.​ This location benefits from its excellent visibility and frontage on the intersection of Warren Rd and N Wayne Rd, major thoroughfares through Westland which boast over 62,300 vehicles per day.​ This is an anchor tenant in the busy the Westland Shopping Center, a major retail destination in Westland.​ This location also includes a Sephora, and Amazon Pick-up and Drop-off Center as part of their new and innovative brand partnerships which contributes to increased foot traffic into the store.​ This site also has dense demographics with over 282,963 residents residing within a 5-Mile radius of the site.​

National retailers in the immediate vicinity include JC Penny, Footlocker, Target, Kay Jewelers, FedEx, Bath & Body Works, Longhorn Steakhouse, Subway, Mattress Firm, Starbucks, CVS, Burlington, Party City, Petco, Sally Beauty, Crunch Fitness, Ashley Furniture, Best Buy, Sonic, McDonald’s, Men’s Wearhouse, Arby’s Chase Bank, Pep Boys, Meijer, Culver’s, Lowe’s, and many more.​ This is an excellent opportunity for an investor looking to purchase a stable, long-term investment with zero landlord responsibility.​

column2: New Offering | Two Grocery-Anchored Community Centers
column3:
SRS Investment Properties Group, as exclusive broker, is pleased to present the opportunity to acquire, either as a Portfolio or individually, Lagniappe Village (202,512± SF grocery-anchored community center) and Iberia Plaza (131,248± SF community center) – two grocery-anchored shopping centers located in the heart of New Iberia, Louisiana.​

New Iberia, LA

Located roughly 20 miles southeast of Lafayette and 68 miles southwest of Baton Rouge, New Iberia serves as the parish seat for Iberia Parish, within the Lafayette, LA MSA.​ Home to a significant healthcare node, oil and gas infrastructure, the Port of Iberia and major installations for companies like Mcllhenny’s (Tabasco) and Halliburton; New Iberia continues to grow along with nearby Lafayette, in the heart of Cajun Country.​

Port of Iberia

·        Strategically located in the heart of Cajun country along the Louisiana Gulf Coast between Houston and New Orleans

·        Direct access to Gulf Intracoastal Waterway and access to the Gulf of Mexico

·        2,000-acre industrial and Manufacturing facility

·        100 oil & gas fabrication companies

·        8,000-ft.​ general aviation airport within 3 miles
column4:
Lagniappe Village

Grocery-anchored by ALDI on a new 10-yr lease - Providing a valuable, essential needs shopping draw for the Property

Anchored by a synergistic mix of value-minded retailers – ALDI, T.J.Maxx, Five Below, Citi Trends and Burke’s Outlet (Pending) - With an avg remaining lease term of 6 years –

Phenomenal, recent leasing momentum at the Property includes new leases with ALDI and Five Below - A pending lease with Burke’s Outlet, a recent 5-yr renewal with PetSmart, a recent expansion by Shoe Dept., and an extension with Citi Trends

Situated across from a Walmart Supercenter and adjacent to Rouses, Hobby Lobby and Ross, Lagniappe Village boasts an advantageous location in the heart of New Iberia’s retail nucleus

11 of 14 non-anchor tenants at the Property boast e-commerce resistant retail uses - Including restaurants, cell phone providers, beauty services, accounting and government tenants

Situated across from a Walmart Supercenter which is ranked in the top 85% nationally and adjacent to Rouses, Hobby Lobby and Ross - Lagniappe Village boasts an advantageous location in the heart of New Iberia’s retail nucleus

Main and main position at the signalized intersection of E Admiral Doyle Dr (LA-674) and S Lewis St, the Property accesses a combined traffic count of 25,605 VPD - Further bolstered by major outparcel draws – Chick-Fil-A, Arby’s, Checkers, O’Reilly Auto Parts, and Tropical Smoothie Café

Iberia Plaza

Grocery-anchored by Super 1 Foods since 2003 - Providing a valuable, essential needs shopping draw for the Property with a long-established consumer base

Having exercised its latest 5-yr option in 2021, Super 1 Foods boasts excellent, growing sales - Of roughly $40M ($500 PSF) - up 15% since 2019

Shadow-anchored by a Walmart Supercenter which is ranked in the top 85% nationally (Placer.ai) - Iberia Plaza benefits from an advantageous location in the heart of New Iberia’s retail nucleus

Based on the current tenant roster, Iberia Plaza boasts over 90% national and strong regional retailers - Bolstered by a shop mix of mostly e-commerce resistant service providers and restaurants

Main and main location adjacent to the signalized intersection of E Admiral Doyle Dr (LA-674) and S Lewis St, the Property accesses a combined traffic count of 25,605 VPD - Further bolstered by excellent visibility and ingress/egress

Horvath & Tremblay is pleased to present the opportunity to purchase Liberty Way West, a new construction retail plaza located at 7560 Blake Street in Liberty Township, Ohio (the “Property”).​ Liberty Way West is comprised of three new construction buildings that consists of a single tenant ground leased Shake Shack, a two-tenant building leased to Torchy’s Tacos and Buff City Soap, and a three-tenant building leased to Robeck’s Juice, Smooth Skin, and Sleep Outfitters.​ The three buildings contain a total of 17,587 square feet and are positioned on a 3.03-acre corner parcel of land.​ Liberty West is 100% occupied; Shake Shack has a 15-year lease, and the other five tenants have new 10-year leases.​ Each of the tenants have triple net leases that feature scheduled rent increases throughout the primary term and renewal options.​

Liberty Way West is shadow anchored by Liberty Center, a new construction lifestyle center that is home to luxury residential apartments, office space, a movie theater, and national and local retailers and restaurants.​ The Property is positioned on the perimeter of Liberty Center and is across the street from a Cabela’s and Chick-fil-A.​ Liberty Way West has outstanding visibility and frontage from Liberty Way, a primary commercial corridor, and is adjacent to Interstate 75.​ The Property is close to two area hospitals, the area’s elementary, middle, and high schools, several larger shopping centers, and new construction residential developments that drive traffic to the area and provide a built-in customer base.​
column4:
NEW CONSTRUCTION: Liberty Way West is comprised of three new construction buildings that consists of a single tenant ground leased Shake Shack, a two-tenant building leased to Torchy’s Tacos and Buff City Soap, and a three-tenant building leased to Robeck’s Juice, Smooth Skin, and Sleep Outfitters. The three buildings contain a total of 17,587 square feet and are positioned on a 4.18-acre corner parcel of land.

LONG TERM LEASES: Shake Shack has a 15-year ground lease with three 5-year renewal options. Torchy’s Tacos, Buff City Soap, Robeck’s Juice, Smooth Skin, and Sleep Outfitters each have 10-year leases with two 5-year renewal options.

MINIMAL LANDLORD RESPONSIBILITIES: Shake Shack has a triple net ground lease, the remainder of the tenants have net leases with the tenants responsible for their pro-rata share of all real estate taxes, insurance, common area maintenance, and repairs to the Property making it an attractive investment for the passive investor, and protecting the in-place cash flow against rising costs of service and labor.

SCHEDULED RENT INCREASES: All of the tenants have scheduled rent increases throughout their primary lease terms, as well as in their option periods, providing a steady increase in income and an attractive hedge against inflation.

OUTSTANDING LOCATION: The Property is positioned on the perimeter of Liberty Center and is across the street from a Cabela’s and Chick-fil-A. Liberty Way West has outstanding visibility and frontage from Liberty Way, a primary commercial corridor, and is adjacent to Interstate 75. The Property is close to two area hospitals, the area’s elementary, middle, and high schools, several larger shopping centers, and several new construction residential developments that drive traffic to the area and provide a built-in customer base.

VISIBILITY & SIGNAGE: Liberty Way West benefits from outstanding visibility and frontage along both Blake Street/Warehouse Row and Liberty Way, the area’s primary commercial corridor. The Property also has two points of access.

AREA DEVELOPMENT: In addition to the growing residential footprint surrounding Liberty Way which includes the Onyx & Obsidian (238 luxury residential apartments), Liberty Flats (356 luxury residential apartments), and the Towns of Wetherington, (70 luxury residential condominiums), the area is also home to Freedom Pointe, an 88-acre planned unit development that is under construction. Freedom Pointe, was approved by the Township in 2021 for 88 acres along Liberty Way. This preliminary planned unit development (PUD) includes a new Costco, apartments, townhomes, office sites, a hotel site, and retail and restaurant sites. In November 2022 Costco Liberty opened their doors with residents lined up outside in anticipation. A new dental office, Affiliates in Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery (AOMS), has since opened and the Relay 129 Hills apartment complex has also begun the construction process.

TRADE AREA: Additional retailers drawing consumers to the trade area include Costco, Lowe’s, Home Depot, Bass Pro Shops, Target, Kroger, Dillard’s, Eddie Bauer, American Eagle, Talbots, Old Navy, Meijer, Aldi, Kohl’s, Michael’s, TJ Maxx, Dick’s Sporting Goods, Planet Fitness, Brio Italian Grille, Cheesecake Factory, Texas Roadhouse, Longhorn Steakhouse, TGI Fridays, Chick-fil-A, Starbucks, McDonald’s, Wendy’s, Burger King, Arby’s, Jack in the Box, Raising Cane’s, Smashburger, McAlister’s Deli, Bob Evans, Noodles & Co, IHOP, Waffle House, Krisy Kreme, Panda Express, Dunkin’, and Subway.

STRONG DEMOGRAPHICS: Over 58,600 people live within 3-miles of the Property with an average household income of over $172,099. More than 142,400 people live within 5-miles of the Property with an average household income of $169,828. Additionally, there are more than 51,100 employees within 5-miles of the Property.

TRAFFIC COUNTS: An average traffic count of over 23,500 vehicles per day pass by the property at the signalized intersection of Liberty Way and Tylers Place Boulevard. An additional 105,900 vehicles pass by the property on Interstate 75.

Loganville Plaza is a 6,800 square foot inline retail center that is shadow anchored by Walmart and Home Depot.​ The property is strategically positioned at the main corner entrance into Walmart with street grade visibility, frontage and full access from highway 78 – a major east-west travel and retail corridor from Atlanta to Athens.​ The average daily traffic counts along highway 78 are approximately 41,800+.​ Loganville is approximately 30 miles east of Atlanta with a surging population of 84k in a five mile radius and projected to grow by 7.6% over the next 5 years.​

The center serves as the only multi-tenant retail center within the power block encompassing Walmart and Home Depot which allows for maximum customer capture.​ The annual customer visits combined between the two anchors is estimated to be over 2.3 Million.​ This area serves as the main retail epicenter for workday and weekend traffic creating a true Monday-Sunday shopping center.​ The current tenant roster features all national tenants on very landlord favorable NNN leases that include management fee reimbursement.​ Moe’s, T-Mobile and GameStop are all original tenants and have occupied the center since inception (2004).​ Jersey Mike’s has been at the center since 2016.​

Marcus & Millichap is pleased to present Metro Health Village Retail in Wyoming, Michigan.​ The subject is an approximately 16,138

square-foot retail strip center with various tenants occupying the buildings; including Starbucks, Marco's Pizza, Posh Nails, Peachwave

Frozen Yogurt, Great Clips, and more.​ The city of Wyoming is just south of Grand Rapids, Michigan and gives the asset great opportunity!

Though commercial establishments are scattered throughout Wyoming today, the greatest concentration is along 28th Street.​ Wyoming City

Hall is there, too---directly across the busy street from Rogers Plaza, the first shopping mall in Kent County.​ Early in its first year as a city,

Wyoming officials sifted through contest entries and selected a motto---City of Vision and Progress.​ It has proved to be an appropriate

choice.​ The city appears to have had 20/20 vision and continues to make great progress.​

Wyoming's population continues to grow.​ Today, Wyoming is Michigan's 16th largest community with west Michigan's third largest

industrial tax base.​ The City has grown to 72,125 strong with a diverse cultural base, seven school districts, a balance of older and modern

homes, retail variety and an abundance of parkland.​ All this takes place in a region that is proud, independent, and growing while still

competitive.​

Jones Lang LaSalle Americas, Inc.​ (“JLL”) is pleased to exclusively offer the Monroe Street Portfolio (the “Property” or “Portfolio”), a 543,378 square foot, dominant collection of open-air shopping centers located in the hyperactive Monroe Street retail corridor in the Toledo MSA.​ The 94% occupied portfolio features an excellent, credit profile and stable, predictable revenue stream with a high performing anchor tenant driving traffic to the Property from the extended trade radius.​ The Property provides investors a tenant lineup with over 4.8 years of weighted average lease term with over 81% of gross income derived from credit and anchor tenancy that include Target, Golf Galaxy, Marshalls, HomeGoods, Five Below, Bob’s Discount Furniture, Petsmart ,Hobby Lobby and more.​

The Monroe Street Portfolio is one of the dominant, center of gravity open air shopping centers in the extended trade area along the Monroe Street Corridor (+22,000 VPD), ranking as the 3rd most visited Property within a 30-mile radius with over +5.0 million visits over the last 12 months.​ The Property has enjoyed significant leasing momentum since 2020 with over +45,200 SF of new leases signed and +83,300 SF of renewals executed.​

The Monroe Street Portfolio offers investors secure, long-term income from an essential tenant base where over 81% of the Property’s gross income is derived from credit and national tenancy at a significant discount to replacement cost.​ The Property is located in an ideal infill location, just 1.9 miles from Route 23 (+70,000 VPD) and 2.0 miles from I-475 (+71,000 VPD), with excellent roadway visibility and transportation infrastructure driving consumers from the extended trade radius, with a 5-mile population of +197,892 and average household income of $72,693.​ The Portfolio is being offered as a whole and in individual pieces.​

Vanwald & Associates is pleased to present the unique opportunity to bid and own the Newberry Shopping Center, located at 110-140 SW 250th ST Newberry, FL.​

The Offering.​ The offering is comprised of one, fully leased  strip center with full frontage near the intersection of Newberry RD and SW 250th.​ Bidding starts on December 4 and ends on December 6.​

153 FT of Frontage.​ The center benefits of about 153 feet of frontage on busy 250th Street near the intersection with Newberry Road.​

Gainesville Metro Area.​ Newberry is a quaint suburb of Gainesville, Florida which is well known as being the home of the University of Florida.​

100% Leased.​ NNN Type Leases.​ The center is 100% leased with NNN leases in place which allow for a full pass-through of expenses.​

Under Market Rents.​ Two of the four leases are under market by about 50% and are due for renewal next year.​ A new owner can realize a significant upside from bringing the leases to current rate.​ A projected $45,000 can be added to the NOI which can result in about $562,000 in equity increase.​

New Roof.​ New HVAC.​ New Paint.​ There is little to no deferred maintenance for a new owner.​ The center is built to last.​ The exterior walls are erected with solid concrete block and a new metal roof was installed in the recent years.​ Metal roofs have an estimated life of about 50 years (according to experts).​ Three of the four units have brand new HVAC units and the center has been re-painted in July of 2023.​

Easy Maintenance.​ Tenants maintain the interior of their premises at their expense and pay CAM for their pro-rata share of operating expenses, taxes and insurance.​

Strategic Location.​ The strategic location and visibility should continue to serve as a catalyst in retaining the existing tenants and attracting new prospects in the future.​

column3: Prime Investment Opportunity: Dive into a lucrative venture with the expansive North Oaks Plaza, boasting a vast 268,893 Sq.​ Ft.​ retail expanse, and a thriving annual Gross revenue surpassing $2,484,000
column4:
North Oaks Plaza spans 268,893 square feet of rentable space, covering roughly 18.33 acres at the meeting point of Natural Bridge Road and Lucas-Hunt Road, positioned at the northeast corner.

• The property features three one-story retail establishments and a three-story office structure. The total retail space available for lease is 268,893 SF, and the office space sums up to 25,023 SF.

• Initially established in 1963, the center has seen significant renovations in the years 1994, 2007, and the latest in 2021. A vast parking area accommodates 4 parking slots for every 1,000 square feet of space, providing tenants a distinctive advantage in such a densely-packed area.

• In 2021, the property benefited from an investment exceeding $3,000,000. This fund facilitated fresh renovations for GSA Social Security and Dedicated Senior Medical Center spaces, parking lot improvements, a new TPO roofing for the Save A Lot outlet, and a fresh paint coat for the plaza and the professional building.

• The plaza is neighbored by standalone outlots, including Walgreens, McDonald’s, and Simmons Bank. These establishments enhance the overall traffic to the plaza and contribute to its vibrancy. As per data from Placer.AI, the McDonald’s outlet ranks in the top 30% of its locations nationwide, and the Walgreens is among the top 15%. However, these outlots aren't included in the plaza's offerings.

• North Oaks Plaza boasts impressive visibility and multiple entrance and exit points, granting convenient access from any route. It has four entryways on Natural Bridge Road (11,295 VPD), one of which is a semi-signalized intersection. The plaza can also be reached through alternate paths, including a rear entrance on O’Neil Avenue via Pasadena Boulevard. Additionally, a fully signalized junction lies close by, at the confluence of Natural Bridge Road and Lucas-Hunt Road, managing the dense traffic of these prominent routes.

column2: 19,550 SF Gun Range & Retail Facility - Opportunity for Multiple Income Streams & Buildable Pad
column3:
The property is a ±19,550 SF two-story gun range with retail and training facilities located in the Southeast submarket.​ The asset is being sold as an owner-user opportunity.​ The building sits on 1.33 acres and is zoned MC within the Henderson city limits.​ There are two points of ingress/egress; one on Boulder Highway and one on King Street.​ The surrounding area includes high traffic with ± 23,000 cars per day on Boulder Highway.​ Nearby, there are several recreational retailers including RVs, boats and ATVs, auto dealerships, casinos, Cowabunga Bay Water Park, and the new Cadence Master-Planned Community boasting an additional 12,250 residential units on 2,200 acres just to the east of the property.​ 


The facility was originally built in 1993 with additional renovations and upgrades in April of 2022.​ The property houses a 9-lane total containment trap (TCT) style shooting range with steel plate backing, a retail area, gunsmith workshop, offices, storage, multiple restrooms, an elevator, high dock loading, training area and classroom space.​ 


All exterior walls of the building are block walls with reinforced concrete cores for added security.​ All exterior doors and windows have motorized metal roll-up coverings and/or metal security gates.​ Ample power is supplied to the building with 1,000 amps and a back up generator.​
column4:
• Opportunity for multiple income streams - existing gun range, classrooms, retail area, & potential long rifle range on 2nd floor

• Street-front buildable pad -  ± 8,500 SF street-front pad with dedicated pylon sign on Boulder Hwy; potential added income

• Capability to add second rifle range - the additional range could double the number of shooting stalls, provide up to 30-yard target depths

Paradise Shoppes of Monroe is a 23,500 square foot class A neighborhood retail center positioned at the major intersection of Highway 138 and West Spring Street - just south of Highway 78, a main travel artery from Atlanta to Athens.​ The immediate area features high attraction tenants such as Walmart Supercenter, Home Depot, Piedmont Walton Hospital and others.​ The retail trade area attracts both resident and transient customers as evidenced by 15.2+ million foot traffic visits over the last 12 months within a 0.5 mile radius.​ Directly adjacent to the subject property is a high volume Chick-fil-A that sees on average over 100k visits per month.​

The subject property consists of two separate parcels.​ Parcel A features a 5,300 square foot freestanding building anchored by Truist Bank and Moe's Southwest Grill.​ Both end cap spaces allow for full drive through capability with Moe's SW Grill utilizing dedicated patio space.​ Parcel B features a 18,200 square foot inline retail building featuring regional tenants such as Little Caesar's, Shane's Rib Shack, Tokyo Sushi & Hibachi and Smoothie King.​ The west end cap of the building has previous approval for use as a drive-through.​ There is an additional 0.37 acre vacant pad between Starbucks and Chick-fil-A that is included in the sale and currently not being utilized.​

Horvath & Tremblay is pleased to present the exclusive opportunity to purchase the Petco Plaza located at 10 Sylvan Street in Peabody, Massachusetts (the “Property”).​ The Property contains a 22,712 square foot retail plaza on a 2.40-acre corner parcel anchored by Petco, and also features leases with Bagel World and Atha’s Roast Beef & Pizza.​ Petco has been at this location for over 24 years and occupies over 76% of the Property.​ Petco extended their lease by 10 years demonstrating their commitment to the site and the market.​ Their current lease has over 6 years remaining on their current lease term followed by two (2), 5-year renewal options.​

Petco Plaza is situated in an exceptional location along the Route 114 corridor, at the well-trafficked, signalized intersection of Sylvan Street and Andover Street (Route 114).​ The Property benefits from excellent visibility and frontage, as well as three points of access and ample parking.​ Petco Plaza is down the street from the Northshore Mall, the dominant shopping center serving Boston’s northeastern suburbs, at the junction of Route 114 and Route 128.​ The entire trade area features an extensive lineup of major national retailers and popular local businesses that make for the preeminent retail destination in Boston’s Northshore.​
column4:
STRONG ANCHOR TENANT: Petco has operated at this location since 1999 (24+ years) and occupies over 76% of the building area. Petco extended their lease by 10 years demonstrating their commitment to the site and the market. Their current lease has over 6 years remaining with two (2), 5-year renewal options. Petco is the second largest pet specialty retail chain in North America with over 1,500 stores and reported net sales of $5.97 billion for 2022.

OUTSTANDING LOCATION: The Property is exceptionally well-located at the well-trafficked, signalized intersection of Sylvan Street and Andover Street (Route 114), with outstanding visibility and frontage on both streets. The location is part of a major trade area between Route 128 and Interstate 95, featuring an extensive lineup of major national retailers and popular local businesses driving significant traffic to the area. The Northshore Mall is down the street from the Property at the junction of Route 114 and 128, and offers an upscale shopping atmosphere with a generous variety of more than 130 specialty stores.

SCHEDULED RENT INCREASES: The Petco lease features scheduled 10% rent increases at the start of each of their two (2), 5-year renewal options. The Bagel World lease features annual 2% rental increases throughout their 5+ year term and option period. Atha’s Roast Beef & Pizza features an 11% rent increase at the start of their renewal option, with annual increases during the option, providing a steady increase in income and an attractive hedge against inflation.

MINIMAL MANAGEMENT RESPONSIBILITIES: Petco, Bagel World, and Atha’s Roast Beef & Pizza reimburse for the majority of their pro-rata share of all real estate taxes, operating expenses, repairs and maintenance to the entire property, making it an attractive investment for the passive investor.

UPSIDE POTENTIAL: The Property offers potential upside through lease-up of a 1,345 square foot vacant suite.

RETAIL TRADE AREA: Additional retailers driving traffic to the trade area include Nordstrom, Life Time Fitness, Target, Market Basket, CVS, Trader Joe’s, Home Depot, Shaw’s, Chase Bank, Bank of America, Starbucks, McDonald’s, Wendy’s, Taco Bell, Dick’s Sporting Goods, Best Buy, Kohl’s, Michaels, TJ Maxx, Nordstrom Rack, Bed Bath & Beyond, Dunkin’, Burlington, At Home, Macy’s, AutoZone, Firestone, Advance Auto Parts, and many others.

STRONG DEMOGRAPHICS: Over 94,700 people live within a 3-mile radius of the Property with an average household income of $101,916, while 215,900+ people live within 5 miles of the Property with an average household income of $107,907.

EXCELLENT TRAFFIC COUNTS: An average traffic count of over 77,600 vehicles per day pass by the Property at the signalized intersection of Sylvan Street and Andover Street (Route 114).

column3:
Horvath & Tremblay is pleased to present the exclusive opportunity to purchase Prospect Plaza located at 480-490 Prospect Road in Oakland Park, Florida (the “Property”).​ The retail plaza contains 5,125 square feet on a 0.60-acre corner parcel and has twenty-five (25) on-site parking spaces.​ The current owner operates Ottographics, which has been in business for 25+ years, and uses three of the retail suites (suites 3, 4, and 5).​ The owner is open to signing a short-term lease at a negotiable rate and term for two of the three units at close of escrow.​ The other two suites have month-to-month tenants.​ Prospect Plaza offers the opportunity to put the existing month-to-month tenants on long term leases at market rates, or to replace them with new long-term tenants.​ The versatile Property is currently configured for five retail suites, but they can be easily combined to accommodate larger spaces, allowing an owner to draw from a larger pool of prospective tenants.​ Also, each unit is individually metered for Electric and Water.​

The Property is well located at the intersection of Prospect Road and NW 5th Avenue and is just seconds from N Andrews Avenue (SR 811A), Powerline Road (SR 845) and Commercial Boulevard (SR 870), the area’s primary east-west commercial and commuter corridor.​ The Property is surrounded by densely populated residential neighborhoods, and heavy commercial development around the Fort Lauderdale Executive Airport (1.75-miles away), and is 1-mile from Interstate 95, 2-miles from Federal Highway (US Route 1) and 4.5-miles from downtown Fort Lauderdale.​ The area is home to numerous national tenants, area schools, and planned communities drawing significant traffic to the area.​
column4:
PROPERTY ZONING: The Property is zoned B-2: General Business District. The B-2: General Business District is intended to apply to certain arterial streets where business establishments may be located to serve large sections of the city and adjacent areas. Such businesses need a conspicuous and accessible location convenient for motorists. Uses are particularly oriented toward meeting the full service needs of city residents. This is one of the most versatile zoning designations and allows for a variety of uses including but not limited to: financial institutions, office space, medical and dental office space, service establishments, retail establishments, and restaurants (carry-out, full-service, sit down, quick-serve).

VALUE ADD OPPORTUNITY: The 5,125 square foot building is situated on a 0.60- acre corner lot along Prospect Road. The Property benefits from excellent visibility and frontage along two roads and ample on-site parking. The versatile Property is currently configured for five retail suites, but they can be easily combined to accommodate larger spaces, allowing an owner to draw from a larger pool of prospective tenants. The Property is also ideal for an owner-user taking advantage of the excellent location of the underlying real estate.

STRATEGIC LOCATION: The Property is well located on Prospect Road and is just seconds from N Andrews Avenue (SR 811A), Powerline Road (SR 845) and Commercial Boulevard (SR 870), the area’s primary east-west commercial and commuter corridor. 480-490 Prospect Road is 1-mile from Interstate 95, 2-miles from Federal Highway (US Route 1), 4-miles from the Florida Turnpike, and 4.5-miles from downtown Fort Lauderdale. The Property also boasts two municipal bus stops 0.3-miles away, one on Powerline Road and one on N Andrews Avenue, and is 1.8-miles from the Cypress Creek Tri-Rail Station and is 8-miles from the Fort Lauderdale-Hollywood International Airport.

AREA RETAILERS: Additional retailers in the area include Home Depot, Lowe’s, Publix, Aldi, Ross, Five Below, Crunch Fitness, Walgreens, Dollar Tree, O’Reilly Auto Parts, AutoZone, Starbucks, Chipotle, McDonald’s, Burger King, Wendy’s, Denny’s, Popeyes, Arby’s, Smoothie King, Miami Grill, Dunkin’, 7-Eleven, and Wawa.

TRAFFIC COUNTS: More than 22,000 vehicles pass the Property along Prospect Road. An additional 150,700+ vehicles pass near the Property daily along Interstate 95.

DEMOGRAPHICS: There are approximately 138,300 people within a three-mile radius of the property with an average household income of $102,633. An impressive 410,000+ people within a 5-mile radius of the property with average household incomes of $99,720. The 5-mile area is also home to more than 287,200 employees.

column3: This offering provides the opportunity to acquire Redwood Village, a 98% occupied retail shopping center in West Jordan, Utah.​ Consisting of 96,615 square feet, the center features established mid box tenants including Harbor Freight Tools, Dollar Tree, and The Warehouse, as well as local boutique shops.​ The asset is situated along the vibrant Redwood Road and 7000 South retail corridors which feature direct access to large employers, housing, and Utah’s interstate freeway system.​
column4:
Potential Pad Site – As a possible value-add opportunity, the center includes a potential pad site for future development (see site plan).

Occupancy and WALT – With average in place rents of approximately $15.25 psf (in-line tenants) and $9.75 psf (anchor tenants), the center is positioned as the low cost provider in the trade area and therefore provides a significant value add opportunity to increase rents. All the anchor stores (51,219 sf, 54% of total occupancy) have been tenants at the center for approximately 15 years or greater. This has helped increase foot-traffic and maintain stable occupancy over time. The property boasts 98% occupancy with 2.5 years of WALT remaining as of 8/1/2023. This provides stable and consistent yield with the ability to strategically implement new tenancy and increase net operating income over time.

Dynamic Retail Location – The center is located just 17 minutes from downtown Salt Lake City and 16 minutes from Salt Lake City International Airport, which is completing its $5.1B expansion and renovation. This asset is situated on Redwood Road which is a main traffic boulevard running north and south and features seamless connectivity to both I-15 and I-215. There are two grocers within a one-block radius, Smith’s Foods and Lucky Stores, both of which generate considerable traffic for the trade area.

Strong Area Demographics – This asset is strategically positioned within 5 miles of 139,557 households with a total population of 405,243 residents that feature strong average household incomes of $99,608. Within a one-mile radius there are 5,866 households with average household incomes of $106,007. Redwood Road and 7000 South serve as the main transportation corridors for these residents with 42,400 vehicles per day on Redwood Road and 26,920 vehicles per day on 7000 South.

Retail Market Resilience – Even in the face of economic challenges, the American consumer has shown resilience. In July 2023, retail sales increased by 0.7% compared to June, and they saw a 3.2% rise from July 2022. On the commercial real estate side, the national retail vacancy rate tightened to 5.4% in Q2 2023. The Salt Lake City retail market’s vacancy stands at 3.9%, among the nation lowest. Meanwhile, asking rents experienced a growth of 4.7% over the past year, reaching $23.47 per square foot.

Santa Clara, California is located in the heart of the Silicon Valley, home to almost 4 million residents.​ Santa Clara has the oldest university in California in Santa Clara University with enrollment over 8,600 students.​ Santa Clara is also home to the San Francisco 49ers at Levi’s Stadium and California’s Great America Amusement Park, which spans 112 acres and has operated since 1976.​ Companies headquartered in Santa Clara include Advanced Micro Devices, Agilent Technologies, Applied Materials, Arista Networks, Chegg, Intel, McAfee, Nvidia, OmniVision Technologies and Veritas Technologies.​ Santa Clara also owns and operates Silicon Valley Power, an electric utility serving over 55,000 residences.​ The average household income in Santa Clara exceeds $140,000.​

column2: Recently Redeveloped Family Dollar and O’Reilly Auto Parts Anchored Center | Odessa, TX
column3:
Sherwood Village is a 82,264 square-foot community shopping center in Odessa, Texas, the epicenter of the United States shale revolution.​ The Property is advantageously located at the signalized intersection of East 42nd Street and Dixie Boulevard, a high-traffic corridor with exposure to over 40,000 cars per day.​

Sherwood Village is 96% leased and anchored by Family Dollar and O’Reilly Auto Parts, along with a diverse collection of e-commerce-resistant and complementary tenants, promoting ample cross-shopping opportunities.​ Further, the center offers an attractive consumer appeal based on a significant redevelopment completed in 2020.​ The major overhaul of the center included roof overlay (with 20-year labor and materials warranty), new plumbing, pylons signs and lighting, major parking lot repairs, and an additional 17,000 square feet of space to satisfy the market’s demand.​

Sherwood Village is an ideal investment that provides an investor with a reliable and stable retail property below replacement costs, providing a valuable entry point for an established retail opportunity while minimizing overall economic risk.​ With the limited availability and low market vacancy, this Property is in a prime position for healthy cash flows for years to come in a market with little pressure from future construction.​
column4:
Advantageous Cost Basis: The ability to acquire the Property well below replacement costs provides investors with a valuable entry point for an established multi-tenant retail opportunity, minimizing overall economic risk.

Extensive Renovation Limiting Future Capital Expenditures: The Property boasts a high-quality curb appeal and provides a substantial leasing advantage compared to other centers in the trade area based on the redevelopment in 2020. The extensive overhaul of the center included roof overlay, new plumbing, pylons signs and lighting, electrical improvements, major parking lot repairs, and an additional inline space.

Secure Income Stream: The Property provides an investor with significant stability based on contractual rent paid by an evenly distributed composition, preventing concentration on one tenant or use. In addition, with nearly six years of weighted average term remaining, it creates a staggered future rollover with only 10.34% of the Property’s GLA expiring within three years.

Strong Development Fundamentals with Prime Retail Location: The Property’s well-designed layout and lack of outparcels increase visibility and accessibility in the heart of Odessa’s main retail corridor.

Broad E-Commerce Resistant Tenant Mix: Sherwood Village’s prime location has made it the top destination for retailers within the trade area, resulting in a diverse collection of national, regional, and local tenants that are e-commerce-resistant and synergistic, creating a dynamic mix.

Thriving Retail Market: As part of the redevelopment, an additional 17,000 square feet of retail was built in 2020 and quickly absorbed, articulating the depth of the Odessa retail market. Odessa enjoys a very low vacancy of 2.10%, resulting in a cumulative rental increase of 12.20% over the past three years that will continue to trend based on minimal new developments, ensuring existing tenant retention and future tenant appeal if space becomes available.

Signalized Intersection with Robust Traffic: Sherwood Village is located on a heavily trafficked signalized intersection of Dixie Boulevard and East 42nd Street, which serves as a primary neighborhood thoroughfare for residents of the mature trade area. The Property’s tenants benefit from a combined 40,000 cars daily at the intersection.

column2: New 10 Year Starbucks & Aspen Dental Retail | Trophy Ft Lauderdale Location
column3:
CBRE’s Net Lease Property Group is pleased to present the opportunity to acquire a new four tenant retail building in the heart of the booming Fort Lauderdale market.​ Fort Lauderdale currently leads the nation in retail rent growth.​

This is a rare opportunity to acquire a newly constructed, 100% leased trophy multitenant retail/medical property at the Northeast signalized hard corner of SE 17th Street Causeway (42,500 AADT) and Miami Road just down the street from the World-Famous PIER 66 at the gateway to Fort Lauderdale Beach.​ There are two newly proposed mixed-use high rise projects on SE 17th Street within walking distance of this property.​ Highly sought after real estate, this location benefits from being in a densely populated upper income area of Fort Lauderdale just south of Downtown and the iconic Las Olas Boulevard.​

Shoppes at Rio Vista is the redevelopment of a 2.59 acre site that had been home to an extremely successful location for Bank of America since 1974.​ Bank of America now has a new 5,540 square foot stand-alone state of the art branch (opened in March of 2021) and ABC Fine Wine & Spirits also has a new 10,244 square foot standalone store (opened in July of 2022).​ This multi-tenant building consists of 9,460 square feet and is home to Starbucks (with drive thru), Aspen Dental, VIO Med Spa and Chip City Cookies.​ The property has multiple access points, monument signage and exceptional on-site parking with a total of 137 spaces (5.95 spaces per 1,000 square feet).​

column2: Maximize Value by Boosting Rents or Re-Developing
column3:
375 NE 54th Street is located a quick turn off of Biscayne Boulevard, Miami’s main corridor.​ The property sits at the intersection of Buena Vista, MiMo and Little Haiti, all growing neighborhoods due to their proximity to the Downtown Core.​ The property is also minutes from the Design District.​

The property consists of two buildings - a two story shopping center and a one story food market.​ The shopping center has 9 units between 650-850 square feet, allowing for optimal per foot rental numbers.​ The food market is renovated and equipped with a hood, grease trap and walk in cooler.​

The property has below market leases.​ A number of the leases are expired with a few more expiration dates on the horizon and demolition/renovation clauses in every lease.​ This offers significant upside for a buyer.​

The property is zoned T6-8-O - allowing for mid rise development.​ It allows for you to build a mixed-use project with 66 multi-family units or 132 hotel units.​ The property is an ideal buy and hold for someone looking to raise rents and cash in on the appreciation of the area before developing.​ A buyer can also elect to tear down the buildings and develop in the more immediate future.​

The property is located in an Opportunity Zone.​ There is also a large neighborhood changing project proposed directly south of the property.​

Addresses Included: 353 NE 54th Street and 375 NE 54th Street

Combined Lot Size: 19,440 SF

Combined Bldg Size: 10,158 SF

Combined Leasable Area: 8,729 SF

Zoning: T6-8-O

Current Uses: Retail, Office, Convenience Store/Fast Food

Allowed Future Uses: Multi-Family, Hotel, Retail, Restaurant, Office, Etc.​.​

Allowed Density: 66 Multi-Family Units, 132 Hotel Units (before bonuses)

Allowed Height: 8 Stories (Before Bonuses)

Current Gross Income: $206,692

Potential Gross Income Year 1: $303,492

Potential Net Income (using Exit Clauses): $378,845

column4:
• ​

    High Traffic Corridor: The Shops on Mercury Blvd can be accessed directly from Mercury Blvd/VA 134, which observes 57,000 vehicles per day and is the primary retail corridor serving Hampton, VA.

  • ​

    Freddy’s Drive-Thru: Freddy’s Frozen Custard’s suite is equipped with a drive-thru, complementing the building’s intrinsic value and allowing for a vast number of backfill opportunities from retailers seeking a drive-thru.

  • ​

    Long Lease Terms: 100% of the GLA has a 10-year primary lease term, ensuring a new investor steady cash flow and limiting rollover risk. Additionally, each leases is embedded with a 10% rent bump in the fifth lease year.

  • ​

    Corporate Guaranty | Banfield Credit: Freddy’s Frozen Custard and Steakburgers’ lease contract (36% of GLA) is backed by a corporate guaranty from Wildcat Steakburgers and is operated by a 30+ unit franchisee. Banfield Pet Hospital, comprising 43% of the GLA, is owned by Mars Incorporated, a $45B company owning brands such as M&Ms, Pedigree, and Orbit gum. Additionally, the Qdoba Mexican eats franchisee at Shops on Mercury Blvd is the chain’s largest franchisee with 97 total locations.

  • ​

    Proximity to Anchor Retail: The subject property is across the street from Peninsula Town Center, a live-work-play community featuring 38 retailers and 808K SF of retail space including JCPenney, Target, Barnes & Noble, and more. The Town Center had 6.5M visits over the past 12 months and ranks in the 99th percentile nationally for foot traffic among all Community Shopping Centers nationwide (data from placer.ai).

  • ​

    Positive Economic Impact from Military Presence: Located as close to 3-miles from the center, Hampton Roads has long served as a robust military community with 15 military installations and 150,000 active duty and civilian personnel currently. The Navy installation alone in Hampton Roads has an economic impact of $15.8B.
