South Lowry Marketplace commands a hard corner location along Highway 83 (Leetsdale Drive) and South Quebec Street and is currently 95% leased to a dynamic mix of grocery, fitness, food and beverage, medical and service-based tenants.​

The Property and its tenants benefit from the surrounding high density Central Denver neighborhoods and commuter traffic.​ The trade area offers strong demographic densities with over 194,000 residents within a 3-mile radius of the Property and features average household incomes in excess of $119,000.​

South Lowry Marketplace is being offered free and clear on an as-is, where-is basis.​

column3: The offering is a partially occupied retail building on a 19,200 square foot lot adjacent to Providence Park.​ The property, being 25% occupied by Next Level Burger on an oversized lot, provides for three different purchase scenarios: 1) a developer can put little additional investment to lease the vacant spaces as-is for a covered land play; 2) an owner-user can occupy the vacant space, having one great tenant to offset the occupancy cost; 3) an investor can re-tenant the vacant spaces and have a high quality retail investment with frontage on two major thoroughfares next to Providence Park.​ For a developer, the site is zoned Central Commercial (CX), which is a high-density commercial zone that allows the tallest buildings in all commercial/mixed-use zones and allows for retail, office, and multifamily uses.​ A 50-yard line location, the Offering works well for any of the three groups: owner-user, value-add investor, or developer.​

column3: Marcus & Millichap's Brown Retail Group has been selected to exclusively market for sale a trophy Starbucks anchored center located in rapidly growing Wenatchee, WA.​ The Property includes the only drive-thru Starbucks in all of Wenatchee and East Wenatchee and is located at the main entrance to Wenatchee's high barrier-to-entry retail trade area.​ The Property is 100% occupied with a mix of four total tenants including Starbucks (since 2005), FedEx (since 2006), Abundant Life Chiropractic (since 2013), and Love Sushi (since 2021).​ The Property benefits from strong visibility to over 35,000 VPD and large pylon signage.​ To go along with the property's highly desirable location, the Wenatchee market currently features a 1.1% retail vacancy rate, per CoStar.​ The Subject property is located near two major national tenants, Wal-Mart and Home Depot, that provide consistent traffic draw to the immediate area.​ The roof was replaced in 2018 and features a 60ml TPO membrane.​ All Tenants at the center operate on NNN leases, minimizing Landlord management/repair responsibility.​ The city has grown by over 10% within the past decade and has a limited amount of available land left to develop making the asset a highly stable retail center with strong appreciation potential.​
column4:
TROPHY STARBUCKS ANCHORED CENTER

The Property includes the only drive-thru Starbucks in all of Wenatchee and East Wenatchee and is located at the main entrance to Wenatchee's high barrier to entry retail trade area. Starbucks has occupied the property since 2005, when the property was built.

100% OCCUPIED WITH DIVERSE TENANT MIX

The Property is 100% occupied with a mix of four total tenants including Starbucks (since 2005), FedEx (since 2006), Abundant Life Chiropractic (since 2013), and Love Sushi (since 2021).

HIGH BARRIER TO ENTRY MARKET WITH 1.1% VACANCY RATE AND 15% RENT GROWTH

Wenatchee MSA currently boasts a 1.1% retail vacancy rate and 15% rent growth over the past three years, per CoStar, making it one of the tightest retail markets in the state of Washington. With only 2.80% retail footprint growth in the past decade, zero square feet of new retail space delivered in the past 12 months, and zero square feet of retail space currently under construction, the development lull creates an incredibly high barrier to entry as demand for space remains high.

HIGH-VISIBILITY LOCATION WITH STRONG TRAFFIC COUNTS (35,000+ VPD)

The Property benefits from strong visibility to over 35,000 VPD and large pylon signage.

BRAND NEW ROOF

The roof was replaced in 2018 and features a 60 mil TPO membrane.

SHADOW ANCHORED BY LARGE NATIONAL TENANTS

The subject property is located near two major national tenants, Wal-Mart and Home Depot, that provide consistent traffic draw to the immediate area.

SCHEDULED RENT INCREASES AND STRONG NOI GROWTH

Each of the tenants at the Property have scheduled rent increases during the firm term and options periods providing for strong contractual NOI growth.

LOW MANAGEMENT CENTER WITH ALL NNN LEASES

All tenants at the center operate on NNN leases, minimizing Landlord management/repair responsibility.

AFFLUENT, HIGH POPULATION GROWTH MARKET

The Property benefits from a population of over 62,000 people within a 5-mile radius, with average household incomes exceeding $85,000. Within a 5-mile radius, the population has grown over 10% since 2010 and is projected to increase by another 3.0% in the next 5 years. Within a 1-mile radius, the population has grown by more than 15% since 2010.

INCOME TAX FREE STATE

Washington State is an Income Tax-Free state.

Colliers is thrilled to introduce this exceptional real estate investment opportunity in the heart of a well-established and highly sought-after neighborhood.​ Sitting at 2241 – 2311 Maple Avenue in Downers Grove, IL, this strip center boasts a rich history of success and is home to prominent anchors such as J.​ C.​ Licht, Just Tires/Goodyear, Anytime Fitness, Dairy Queen, and other reputable businesses.​

Positioned at the Southwest corner of Maple and Belmont Avenues just east of I-355, this property capitalizes on Downers Grove’s mature and affluent community.​ The property’s location benefits from local commuter patterns in addition to the Belmont train station, I-355 & I-88.​ In addition, the property sits just south of the 300-acre Ellsworth Industrial Park which boasts more than 130 tenants.​ The area is renowned for its prosperity, with a substantial and well-to-do population.​ The property enjoys the benefits of a robust demographic profile, with over 92,000 residents residing within a three-mile radius and an impressive average household income exceeding $132,000.​

This exceptional strip center is now available for acquisition at a competitive price of $6,032,720 offering a compelling 7.50% cap rate.​ With its proven track record, prime location, and strong market fundamentals, this investment opportunity represents a solid and stable addition to any portfolio in an immensely desirable neighborhood.​ Don’t miss out on the chance to become a part of this thriving community and seize this prime investment offering.​

Ackman-Ziff Real Estate Group, as exclusive agent for Ownership, is pleased to offer for sale the fee simple interest in Sumter Square (“Property”), a ±67,000 SF grocery-anchored shopping center in Sumter, South Carolina.​ The Property is 85% leased to a high productivity Piggly Wiggly, Family Dollar, and three small shop tenants.​

The Property is situated at the corner of Broad Street and Bultman Drive, a high-traffic corner with visibility to over 33,000 vehicles daily, and immediately adjacent to the Belk’s-anchored Sumter Mall and the Beacon Multiplex.​ Shaw Air Force Base, the region’s largest employer, is located just 15 minutes west of the center.​

Sumter Square offers investors both a reliable cash flow and the opportunity to create significant value through lease up of two available endcap units.​ Piggly Wiggly, which generated sales of $20MM at this location in 2022, recently signed a long-term extension through 2029, and Family Dollar has operated at the Property for nearly 40 years.​ The existing leases have over 5 years of weighted average term remaining.​

This subject property is located on Judson Road with 20,805 vehicles per day and excellent visibility off of East Loop 281 with 39,298 vehicles per day.​ Tall Pines Center is in a desirable demographic area with a population exceeding 82,720 residents within a five-mile radius, and an average household income of $66,434 within a five-mile radius.​ The subject property is situated next to the Longview Mall, across the street from a Dollar General, and just down the road from numerous national and regional tenants including Walmart Supercenter, Target, Home Depot, Lowe's, Albertson's, and many more.​

column3:
Horvath & Tremblay is pleased to present the exclusive opportunity to purchase The Fountains at Town Center, a retail center located at 1021 Fountain View Drive in Carol Springs, Illinois (the “Property”).​ Originally constructed in 2006, the center contains 27,050 square feet of gross leasable area on a large 3.27-acre parcel.​ The Property is 92.07% leased to a complimentary mix of nine (9) tenants that serve the needs of the local residents.​

The highly visible Property is strategically located along W Lies Road, one of the region’s primary commuter corridors 500 feet from the signalized intersection with N Gary Avenue.​ The Property enjoys three points of access and outstanding visibility from W Lies Road and is close to national retailers, large-scale shopping centers and densely developed residential neighborhoods.​ The Property is a short distance from a busy retail area along West Army Trail Road, which offers a number of retail, dining, entertainment and lifestyle amenities, as well as the Stratford Square Mall.​ Carol Stream is also home to a large concentration of business operations, which bring a large employee population to the area.​

Carol Stream is located in DuPage County, approximately 30 miles west of Chicago.​ DuPage County is the second largest in Illinois (behind Cook County) and one of the most affluent in the state.​
column4:
ASSET: The Fountains at Town Center is an 11-tenant retail center constructed in 2006. The Property consists of two well maintained and attractive retail buildings totaling 27,050 square feet with three points of access, abundant parking. The 3.27-acre parcel offers outstanding visibility and frontage along W Lies Road.

STRATEGIC LOCATION: The highly visible Property is strategically located along W Lies Road, one of the region’s primary commuter corridors, and is 500 feet from the signalized intersection with N Gary Avenue. N Gary Avenue connects the Property with W Army Trail Road to the north and North Avenue to the south, and also is the western boundary of a large business and industrial district in between the two major retail corridors. The Property is close to national retailers, large-scale shopping centers and densely developed residential neighborhoods.

BUILT-IN CUSTOMER BASE: In addition to the densely developed neighborhoods nearby, the Property is positioned at the entrance to The Fountains at Town Center, a town home community built in the mid 2010's by Town and Country Homes. The Fountains at Town Center features 145 beautifully constructed town houses with floor plans ranging from 2,107 to 2,548 square feet of living space.

PROMINENT ACCESS AND VISIBILITY: The Property is located at the at the intersection of W Lies Road and Fountain View Drive with outstanding visibility and frontage along both. The beautifully maintained and landscaped center lines both sides of Fountain View Drive and also serves as a formal entryway to the abutting Fountains at Town Center luxury residential community.

ATTRACTIVE RENT ROLL: The Property is currently 92.07% leased to an attractive mix of tenants (including four restaurants, a hair salon, a nail salon, a dry cleaner, and a liquor store) that serve the surrounding community and draw traffic to the property. The center has 2,145 square feet of vacant space (two suites), that offer the opportunity to add value via lease up.

SCHEDULED RENT INCREASES: Five of the Tenants have scheduled rent increases in either their primary lease terms, or at the start of each of their option periods providing a steady increase in income and an attractive hedge against inflation.

ECONOMIC TRADE AREA: The Property is just seconds from a large industrial/business district located between N Gary Avenue and Schmale Road. The large business and industrial parks are home to more than 100 businesses including Ingram Micro, Assa Abloy, FIC America Corp, Demar Logistics, Inc, FIC America Corp, UPS, Owens & Minor, International Paper, Prinova USA, USPS Regional Center, Benjamin Moore Manufacturing Facility, Office Depot Manufacturing Facility, and Beacon Building Products. These businesses employ thousands of people and are just seconds away from The Property.

IMPRESSIVE DEMOGRAPHICS: Over 102,000 people live within 3-miles of the Property with an average household income of $115,361. An impressive 250,700 people live within 5-miles of the Property with an average household income of approximately $122,075. Additionally, there are more than 47,200 employees within 3-miles of the Property.

TRAFFIC COUNTS: Approximately 9,800 vehicles pass by the Property each day along W Lies Road. More than 32,800 vehicles per day pass through the adjacent intersection of W Lies Road and N Gary Avenue.

DUPAGE COUNTY: Carol Stream is located in DuPage County, which has considerably less tax exposure than neighboring Cook County. This makes it a more desired sub-market for Chicago commercial real estate. DuPage County has over 1,092,400 residents with an average household income of $131,242 producing strong spending power in Carol Stream and the surrounding communities.

Buyer Brokers Protected!

RJBrunelli & Co.​ has been retained by the owner to sell the 100% fee simple interest in The Gardens, the dominant Power Center located in Flanders, New Jersey where interstate Route 80, U.​S.​ Route 46, and Route 206 meet.​ The Power Center is 378,385  square feet not including Walmart, a 141,000 square foot shadow anchor.​ Big Box and sub-anchor merchants include Lowes, Home Goods, Ross, TJ Maxx, Michaels, and PetSmart.​ This high-quality asset, with 93% being credit tenants, is an attractive real estate investment based on the following attributes:

Location: 10-50 International Dr.​ S, Flanders, NJ 07836   

GLA:  378,385 SF

Land Acreage: 46.5 AC

Anchors:  Walmart (NAP), Lowes

Asking Price:  Unpriced

Sub-Anchors: Ross, Home Goods, Petsmart, Michaels, TJ Maxx, Fitness Factory

Non-Owned Parcels:  Walmart, Picatinny Federal Credit Union

Occupancy:  98%

Year Built:  2001 (Renovated 2023)
column4:
STRONG PERFORMING CREDIT TENANCY – The Gardens benefits from a diverse national credit tenant line-up including Lowes, TJ Maxx, PetSmart, Michaels, Home Goods, and Ross, as well as a solid group of local and regional tenants that provide substantial draws to the center. The Gardens offers an investor the security of 28 Tenants, 93% of which have strong credit guaranteeing the leases.

EXCELLENT REGIONAL ACCESS – The Gardens is located on International Drive with immediate access to Rt. 80 with a traffic count of 85,000 vehicles per day, Rt. 46 vehicles per day of 35,000, and Rt. 206 with vehicles per day of 24,000. The subject center draws customers from Roxbury, Ledgewood, Chester, Hackettstown, Netcong, Mt. Arlington, Dover, and Randolph.

SIGNIFICANT BARRIERS TO ENTRY - A mountainous area with significant bedrock creates physical and financial obstacles to additional retail development.

LEASE EXTENSIONS & RENOVATIONS — Lowes, McDonald’s, Michaels, Wendy’s, Applebee’s, Famous Footwear, and T-Mobile recently extended their leases between 5-20 years by the current owner as part of its property renovation and re-leasing accomplishments. Lowe’s as the anchor tenant is paying significantly under-market rent a $4 sq. Ft.. Danielle Brunelli, president of R.JBrunelli & Co., orchestrated the new leases signed including Home Goods, Ross, Boot Barn, Chipotle, Panda Express, Skechers, and Fitness Factory following the sale of the property to the current owner in December 2021. The only remaining vacancy is a 4,800 sq. Ft. end cap space across from Walmart.

  • ​

    Lowe’s is paying below-market rent at $4 sq. Ft. on a long-term ground lease.

  • ​

    The WAULT (Weighted Average Unexpired Lease Term) of The Gardens is approx. 9.3 years providing a long-term steady income stream with low-risk provided by Lease Probe. 

  • ​

    The Gardens recently underwent millions in renovations including but not limited to storefront facade, parking lot re-striping/surfacing, and landscaping.

  • ​

    Nearly 3.5 million visits annually, ranking the Property in the top 12% of shopping centers in New Jersey and top 11% Nationally in 2021 (Placer.ai).

  • ​

    The Property being sold is 378,385  SF on +/- 46.5 acres, this does not include the Walmart shadow anchor.

  • ​

    10-Mile Average Household Incomes are $162,000 and are projected to grow to $179,000 over the next 5 years.

Cushman & Wakefield’s Retail Investment Advisors, are pleased to present the opportunity to acquire The Landing at Town Crossroads (the “Property”), a 32,915 square foot strip center shadowed by Town Square Las Vegas.​ The Property is located on the northwest corner of Interstate 215 (Bruce Woodbury Beltway) and Las Vegas Boulevard in Las Vegas, Nevada.​

The Property is situated on approximately 2.3 acres of land only minutes from the Las Vegas Strip.​ The Landing at Town Crossroads is currently 100% leased to an assortment of complimentary ‘daily-needs’ tenants offering multiple specialty shops and several dining options.​ Approximately over 225,000 vehicles passing the Property daily along Interstate 215 and Las Vegas Boulevard combined.​

The Landing at Town Crossroads is located directly south of Town Square Las Vegas, an approximately 1.2 million square foot lifestyle center that boosted over 9,000,000 visitors within the past 12 months.​ Town Square is anchored by Whole Foods, AMC Theaters, Old Navy, H&M, TJ Maxx, Apple, The Container Store and Guitar Center to name a few of the large scale tenants.​

column2: Multi-tenant Retail Investment Opportunity In Encinitas Trade Area
column3: CBRE is pleased to present a unique opportunity to acquire 90 N Coast Hwy 101 in the Encinitas trade area, a high profile commercial condo, 93% leased multi tenant asset.​ With a core location in the heart of Encinitas, walking distance to the renowned Moonlight Beach.​ The site is conveniently located on Highway 101, the main retail artery for this affluent beach community.​ Sitting at the entrance to Moonlight Beach at B street, at the intersection of Encinitas Blvd and Coast Hwy 101.​ The investment has top visibility, access and parking, in one of the most dynamic retail corridors in Southern CA and benefits from high traffic from both locals and visitors.​
column4:
UNIQUE COASTAL LOCATION

Located two short blocks is Moonlight Beach, considered to be one of the finest beaches in southern California and the center of recreation and social life in Encinitas. This sand beach has numerous convenient facilities including volleyball courts, playground equipment, tennis courts, picnic facilities, restrooms and showers, lifeguards, fire pits and snack bar. From Moonlight Beach, you can walk along the beach for miles in either direction. World famous Swami’s Beach is just a short walk along the beach to the south. Swami’s Surf Beach, made famous by the Beach Boys in “Surfin’ USA,” still draws the finest surfers in the world on a daily basis.

WALKABLE LOCATION

The Lofts at Moonlight Beach is just a short walk from the Downtown 101 shopping district, which features historic architecture, quaint shops, sidewalk cafés, and restaurants. The site is also within walking distance to the Encinitas Coaster station, providing commuter train service between Oceanside and downtown San Diego. The Coaster line connects to Amtrak’s Pacific Surfliner Trains at the Solana Beach station. Other walkable locations include the public library offering a host of programs that are well-attended by the community and meet a variety of interests.

DEBT FREE

The site allows the investor the ability to obtain new financing at attractive terms, enhancing leveraged cash on cash returns.

E-COMMERCE RESISTANT

Retail and professional services represented at the site includes health and beauty, medical services, pet grooming and restaurant uses. These categories have proven to be difficult to replicate online and ensure the centers long term vitality.

OFF STREET PARKING

The center has 21 dedicated spaces in the underground garage for the commercial tenants and customers. There are also parallel public parking spaces along the frontage on Encinitas blvd. and along A Street to the north of the property.

HIGH TRAFFIC

You can’t beat this location if you are a restaurant or retailer looking for a prime coastal San Diego presence. With an established growing community, the site caters heavily to residents while benefiting from a solid daytime and visitor population.

Highway 101.....................±20,200ADT

Encinitas Blvd..................±19,498 ADT

B St......................................±2,955 ADT

Welcome to a rare and exceptional investment opportunity in the heart of Scottsdale, Arizona, at the prestigious Sky Song Innovation Campus.​ Presenting a 4-tenant retail building with a total of 12,002 square feet of prime commercial space.​ This property is currently 100% leased to four thriving restaurants, offering investors the perfect blend of stable, long-term cash flow and exciting upside potential in rental rates.​

Situated in the vibrant city of Scottsdale, this retail property enjoys a strategic location within the renowned Sky Song Innovation Campus.​ This cutting-edge tech hub attracts a diverse and affluent customer base, ensuring consistent foot traffic and robust demand for retail services.​

All four restaurant tenants have established themselves as popular dining destinations, providing a steady stream of rental income.​ With a well-diversified tenant mix, you can feel confident in the property’s resilience even during market fluctuations.​

As the Scottsdale market continues to grow and evolve, this property offers an excellent opportunity for investors to benefit from increasing rental rates in the future.​ With the potential for lease renewals and the strong demand for retail space in the area, your investment is poised for appreciation.​

Don’t miss your chance to invest in a prime retail property in one of Arizona’s most sought-after locations.​ Whether you’re a seasoned investor seeking stable returns or looking to capitalize on the rising rental market, this property offers the best of both worlds.​ Invest in your future with this exceptional commercial real estate opportunity in Scottsdale, Arizona!

column3:
Lee & Associates is pleased to present for sale the Fee Simple interest in “The Shoppes at Meadowview”.​ The subject property consists of a 15.14 acre site improved with 133,157 SF of retail space.​ The property is currently 66.7% occupied, creating the opportunity to add value through the lease up of the vacancy.​ The subject property is one of the largest and most diverse retail properties in Kankakee, IL less than 60 miles from downtown Chicago.​ Meadowview has a diverse and unique merchandise mix focused on essential needs based tenants.​ With a focus on fitness, discount retail and food and beverage, Meadowview has the ideal co-tenancy to attract best of class tenants during the stabilization and lease up process.​ Meadowview will trade far below replacement cost providing a low basis to a new investor looking to achieve an above market yield during the hold / repositioning period and will further recognizing a significant return on equity at exit.​

The Shoppes at Meadowview has attractive in place financing that can be assumed.​ The loan originated in 2021 with an original funding of $4,450,000 and benefits from an attractive below market 4% rate through 11/18/2026 then has a reset to 325 bps over the five-year treasury.​ The debt amortizes on a 25-year schedule.​ The term is 10 years and has a maturity date of 11/17/2023.​ An investor has the ability to assume the in-place debt benefiting from the below market 4% rate with a runway of nearly 3 years to affect the reposition in advance of the reset and look to exit the deal or originate new permanent financing.​

The Shoppes at Meadowview is a rare opportunity to acquire a retail asset with a true value add strategy less than 60 miles from Chicago.​ With exceptional visibility, strong fundamentals and the ability to assume debt with a below market rate, the Shoppes at Meadowview is the preeminent add value retail opportunity in the greater Chicago area.​

Lee & Associates is pleased to present to qualified investors the opportunity to acquire the Fee Simple interest in The Shoppes at Pittsburgh Mills, (“The Property”).​ The Shoppes at Pittsburgh Mills is a 9,907 SF, 100% occupied service retail strip center located in Pittsburgh’s Northeastern suburb of Tarentum.​ The property is strategically located off Route 28 which sees an average 42,000 VPD and is positioned well in the heart of the Pittsburgh Mills retail submarket.​ The Shoppes at Pittsburgh Mills is additionally shadowed by The Galleria at Pittsburgh Mills Mall and top retail tenants such as Walmart, Sam’s Club, Aldi, Lowe’s and many more.​

The property benefits from a superior merchandising mix and is comprised of a diverse group of e-commerce proof tenants.​ The property is anchored with a brand new 10 year corporate Verizon lease and Mattress Firm which represent over 61% of the GLA.​

The Service Retail asset class has outperformed other retail asset classes since the onset of the pandemic.​ The desirable e-commerce proof tenants coupled with a brand new 10-Year lease from Verizon makes the Shoppes at Pittsburgh Mills a perfect vehicle to deliver an above market risk adjusted return with a stable and predictable income stream.​
column4:

  • ​

    Recent Improvements – The property has been successfully repositioned to make way for a flagship Verizon location. The property benefits from a brand new parking lot and façade improvements mitigating exposure to near term deferred maintenance.

  • ​

column2: Core Strip Center in Downtown Riverside
column3: Progressive Real Estate Partners is pleased to present the opportunity to acquire the Shops at University Square— a 100% occupied commercial strip center leased to 6 high performing and diverse service tenants.​ The property is situated in Downtown Riverside, which is currently undergoing a renaissance with an estimated $330 million of recently completed and ongoing retail, hotel, and public works projects driving significant traffic to the property.​ The property features fully NNN leases with embedded 3% annual increases, a diverse income stream with no individual tenant accounting for more than 24% of the center’s income, and ideal space sizes ranging from 750 SF to 1,750 SF (larger tenant pool leading to lower vacancy risk).​ The entire shopping center, including the subject property, was recently remodeled with a new façade.​
column4:
HIGH TRAFFIC STRIP CENTER - STRONG INVESTMENT FUNDAMENTALS

100% Leased to 6 E-Commerce Resistant Tenants – The asset features a robust mix of internet resilient tenants whose uses cannot be easily duplicated online. Examples include RAD Coffee, Miss Donuts & Bagel, and Mariscos Taco Shop.

Fully NNN Leases – All of the center’s tenants are on industry standard AIR NNN leases with no caps on property taxes, insurance, or CAM.

Diverse Tenant Mix – Unlike a single tenant asset where all the asset’s income is tied to one lease, the subject property’s income is spread across 6 tenants with no individual tenant accounting for more than 24% of the center’s income.

Strong Income Growth – All leases feature embedded 3% annual increases. The all-cash yield grows to an estimated 7.00% by 2027.

Limited Shop Space Competition – Strip centers (with parking included) are limited in Downtown Riverside, resulting in less competition and lower vacancy rates.

Ideal Space Sizes Ranging from 750 SF to 1,750 SF – Retail space under 2,500 SF tends to have the largest pool of replacement tenants, reducing vacancy risk and creating more upside potential as supply remains limited.

IRREPLACABLE DOWNTOWN RIVERSIDE LOCATION

Downtown Riverside Has Undergone a MAJOR Renaissance – Recent projects include:

o Riverside Convention Center Remodel ($36 million)

o Brand New Riverside Main Library ($40 million)

o Riverside Culinary Academy ($28 million)

o Fox Theater Event Center ($32 million)

o Cheech Center/Riverside Art Museum ($13 million)

o Imperial Hardware Lofts (89 units)

o The Mark Luxury Apartments (162 units)

o CIRCA on Mission (13 luxury townhomes)

o Mission Heritage Plaza (72 units + retail)

o Riverside Food Lab (14 unique restaurants)

o Several new hotels recently completed and under construction (500+ new rooms)

Recent Facelift – The entire shopping center, including the subject property, was recently remodeled with a new façade.

Adjacent by Established Community Grocery Store – Maxi Foods has operated at the site for over 20 years. As the only grocery store located in Downtown Riverside, it has become vital to the area’s residents and draws significant traffic to the site.

RAD Coffee Recently Added – With over 147,000 followers on Instagram and 4 locations across Southern California (and growing), RAD Coffee draws significant positive traffic to the center.

Highly Visible & Easily Accessible – The subject property benefits from strong visibility along University Avenue, the primary thoroughfare serving Downtown Riverside, ultimately connecting the Downtown Area to UC Riverside.

column3:
SVN proudly presents this amazing investment opportunity in Oak Forest along busy Cicero Ave.​ This three-unit fully occupied shopping center houses two historic tenants who are prominent in the area.​ Tenants have been at this location for many years, however, they entered short-term leases during Covid.​ C&M Awards only occupies half of 14814's front retail space.​ There is room for an additional tenant to share the space, or the new owner could lease the entire space for more than what is currently being collected.​ There is a small basement, laundry room, and one drive-in-door attached to the main retail building.​ Additionally, this sale will include a two-unit rental house which is located behind the retail building.​ Originally built as a home for the previous owner then converted into a rental when the current owner took over.​

Both buildings have been meticulously maintained and the retail building boasts a newer facade and regularly restriped parking lot.​ This property also includes a marquis sign for enhanced street visibility.​ There is ample parking in the front and the back of the building.​ Easy plug-and-play for the right investor, or potential live-where-you-work scenario.​ The seller also has an assumable mortgage at 4.95% interest.​ The taxes are currently being appealed.​ The building is in a TIF district.​

column2: Market Dominant Grocer with Recent Lease Extension
column3:
Cushman & Wakefield Retail Investment Advisors present Townes Crossing (the Property), a 105,731 square-foot grocery-anchored neighborhood center located in Oswego, Illinois, 40 miles west of downtown Chicago.​ The Property is 91% occupied and located on 12.73 AC at the busy signalized intersection of U.​S.​ Highway 30 and Douglas Road (42,000 VPD).​ Located in growing Kendall County, the Property benefits from strong Oswego demographics of 237,374 residents with an average household income of $107,187 within five miles.​ In addition, the Village of Oswego has approved the development of 490 single-family homes and 321 multi-family units on 227 acres approximately 2.1 miles south of the Property.​

At 65,000 SF, Jewel Osco serves as the grocery anchor of Townes Crossing and recently exercised a 5-year renewal option, extending the lease term through November 2029.​ The trailing twelve month’s sales are 36% greater than sales in 2018.​ The market-dominant grocer receives 900K visits annually and is ranked #2 out of 15 grocery properties in a 5-mile radius (according to Placer.​ai).​ The remaining small shop tenancy is made up of a mix of national and regional tenants.​ This offering includes one building anchored by Jewel Osco with small shop space fronting both U.​S.​ Highway 30 and Douglas Road.​

column2: 6.15% Cap | Relocation/New Construction 14 Year Lease | Strong Corporate Guaranty
column3:
Relocation Store/New Construction & Long-Term Lease – This high-quality construction asset was recently completed in 2022, offering a 15-year lease, with ±14 years remaining and multiple renewal options.​ Tractor Supply has operated in this market for many years proving the concept and desire for them to have a brand-new store with a long term commitment to this market.​

New Initiatives Store – The development of the store included Tractor Supply’s preferred “New Initiatives” improvements, with an enlarged Fenced Outdoor Display Area, a greenhouse and a feed room.​

Strong Fortune 500 Tenant – Ranked #291 on the Fortune 500 list, TSC is one of the fastest-rising companies, with their continued impressive growth trajectory, boasting a ±$24.5 billion market cap, and over 2,100 locations.​

TSC Company Growth and E-Commerce Proof – Tractor Supply serves as the industry leader for its ability to adapt and thrive amongst the presence of e-commerce.​ TSC reported net sales increased 20.7% to $4.01 billion in the 4th quarter of 2022 from $3.32 billion in the 4th quarter of 2021.​ This is due in large part to TSC’s investment in their bricks-and-mortar locations and new initiatives such as a buy-online pick-up in-store (curbside pickup), and offering customers same-day delivery from 100% of their stores (the nation’s first general merchandise retailer to do so).​

Corporate Guaranty with Rent Increases – This long-term lease is corporately guaranteed by Tractor Supply Company and encompasses 5% rent increases every 5 years throughout the initial term and option periods to provide some hedge against inflation and a reliable source of income.​

Prime Traffic Location – This asset is conveniently situated along State Highway 23 neighboring national/major tenants nearby such as Lowe’s Home Improvement, Hannaford, BJ’s Wholesale Club, Walgreens, Price Chopper, Walmart Supercenter, Toyota, Ford, Hyundai, Enterprise, Chrysler, Dodge, Jeep, Ram, ALDI, Buffalo Wild Wings, Speedway, The Home Depot, Five Guys, Panera Bread, Burger King, Southside Mall Cinemas, and even the Southside Mall.​

Pandemic Proof Essential Retailer – Tractor Supply proved its resiliency through the COVID-19 pandemic, reporting record financial and operating results in 2020 including a 53% increase in sales since pre-pandemic levels.​

Education in Oneonta – Home to SUNY Oneonta University, which was just rated one of the ‘Best Colleges in America’ by Money.​com, with 6,000 enrolled and Hartwick College, with another 1,500 enrolled sit just a few miles away.​

column3: Robust Commercial building on the square in downtown Carrollton.​ Currently known as Trunks and Treasures, this 3 story historical building is a great opportunity for small business owners.​ The property is zoned B1 commercial and used as a retail antique store.​ The building is historic and believed to be built in 1841.​ Many updates and renovations have taken place such as a new metal roof, new vinyl windows throughout the building, and the first and second floor being totally redone with insulated walls and drywall, new electric and drop ceilings installed.​ There is still a 3rd floor that could be finished for more retail space or apartment areas.​ Newer gas furnace has been installed and ductwork ran to the second floor.​ Beautiful wide main stair case is original and in great shape.​ Large timber beam construction makes this building stout and longterm.​ 1/2 bath on main floor being remodeled currently.​ Street parking is available on the public square.​ Great opportunity for a beautiful historic building and small business.​

This value add strip center in the heart of Garden Grove is ready for an owner to properly manage the property as the tenant mix can be improved, rents are under market and the owner is not collecting CAM.​ The property consists of 4 buildings and tenants totaling 21,368 SF on a large 1.87 acre lot which would allow for development opportunity.​ There are 3 restaurant/café tenants that drive traffic to the property.​ There is great upside potential with increased rent and CAM reimbursement as the tenants were mostly leased up during the Pandemic.​ Property is 100% leased with some tenant leases expired or expiring soon.​

Asking $7,950,000 which translates into a 5.25% as-is cap rate and 6.52% proforma cap rate not including CAM reimbursement.​  We are in the process improving the financials and aesthetic of the property and these improvements should show in the next month or two.​

column3:
HIGH TRAFFIC STRIP CENTER WITH BELOW MARKET RENTS

  • ​

    Below Market, Short Term Leases – 4 of the property’s 5 tenants are on Modified Gross leases with less than 2 months-3.5 years of term remaining.​ The average lease rate amongst these tenants is $1.29 on a net basis, well below the current market lease rate of $2.25 to $2.35/SF + NNN.​

  • ​

    Strong Existing Cash Flow in Addition to Upside – The center features a “going-in” 5.00% all-cash yield with an estimated 8.00% proforma yield with market rents.​

  • ​

    3.60% Retail Vacancy Rate – Azusa Avenue features one of Southern California’s lowest retail vacancy rates at 3.60% (compared to LA County at 5.40%, Orange County at 4.50%, and the Inland Empire at 5.90%) (Source: CoStar).​

  • ​

    0.30% Shop Space Vacancy – Amongst the estimated 1.5M SF of retail properties along Azusa Avenue (between the 10 Freeway & Covina Blvd), there are only 3 vacancies for shop spaces between 1,000 SF to 2,000 SF (Source: CoStar).​

  • ​

    Located Along THE Commercial Corridor for the Trade Area – Azusa Avenue serves is the primary north/south thoroughfare for residents and shoppers in West Covina.​ Surrounding tenants include: West Covina Jeep, McDonald’s, Stater Bros.​ Markets, Food 4 Less, Chase Bank, Norm’s, CVS, El Pollo Loco, Wells Fargo, Denny’s, 7 Eleven, and more.​

STRONG RETAIL FUNDAMENTALS

  • ​

    100% Leased to 5 E-Commerce Resistant Tenants – The asset’s tenant mix features a robust mix of internet resilient tenants, including: nail salon, hair salon, taekwondo, massage, and Friar Tux.​

  • ​

    Below Replacement Cost at $334/SF – With construction costs currently hovering near $500/SF (not including the cost of land), the subject property is priced well below replacement cost at $334/SF (particularly when accounting for the value of the underlying land).​

  • ​

    Recent Improvements – The property received a new roof in 2019 and new parking lot security gates in 2022.​

  • ​

    Diverse Income Stream – Unlike a single tenant asset where all the asset’s income is tied to one lease, the subject property’s income is spread across 5 tenants with no individual tenant accounting for more than 27% of the center’s income.​

  • ​

    Visibility to ±53,909 Cars Per Day on Azusa Avenue

  • ​

    135 Feet of Frontage – The property and its tenants are positioned with maximum visibility to Azusa Avenue with no clear obstructions to the center’s visibility.​

  • ​

    Strong Historical Occupancy - Majority of the property's tenants have been at the property for 10 years or longer.​

Vickery Athletics & Lilac Tattoo Studio At Cityplace is a 7,204 SF two tenant asset adjacent to Cityplace Tower, The Central Development and Uptown Dallas.​ Positioned just east of Highway 75 adjacent to exciting new construction high rise and mid rise apartments, the Property is just minutes from Downtown Dallas on Belmont Avenue.​ Vickery Athletics & Lilac Tattoo Studio At Cityplace is currently 100% leased with rents averaging $18.07 PSF NNN with an average base lease expiration of December 2027 presenting upside meaningful opportunity.​ The average household income is over $131,100, $140,300 & $130,900 within a 1, 3 and 5 mile radii, respectively.​ Notable retailers in the immediate area include Kroger, Target, Office Max, Walmart, LA Fitness, PetSmart, Ross, CVS and Whataburger, amongst others.​

Positioned in a highly desirous residential, investor and developer attractive area of East Dallas, the Property benefits from its location nearby Cityplace just east of Highway 75, as well as convenient access to the Dallas Central Business District, Baylor Hospital, Uptown, Deep Ellum, Knox-Henderson, Highland Park, University Park and numerous other DFW destinations.​

column2: Chesapeake Service Retail | 8.7+ Yr Tenant Tenure | Primary Retail Node
column4:
• ​

    Primary Retail Node – Proximity to National Anchor Retail: The subject property is positioned adjacent to a power center with national anchor retailers Walmart Supercenter, At Home, Sam’s Club and Dollar Tree. The center draws 3.5M visits annually and has strong foot traffic with the At Home and Dollar Tree ranked in the 98th and 86th percentile nationally in terms of foot traffic among all locations (data from Placer.ai). Additionally, Walmart Way is one exit down from Greenbrier Mall, home to Macy’s, JCPenney, and Dillard’s and observing 2.6M visits annually.

  • ​

    Access From I-64 and VA-168: The shops are less than a mile from an interchange of I-64, which observes 116,000 vehicles per day and is the primary east-west connector between West Virginia and Hampton Roads through Charlottesville and Richmond. The center is just off VA-168 (63,000 VPD), a primary South Hampton Roads connector.

  • ​

    Strong Operating History: The current tenant lineup at Walmart Way Crossing has an average weighted tenure at the center of 8.7+ years with 42% of the GLA leasing space at the center for 10+ years, proving a desirability for the space and a tenant commitment to the site. Additionally, the rent roll features corporate leases for America’s Best Contacts, H&R Block, and Direct Auto Insurance as well as a 16-unit franchisee for Great Clips and a 9-unit operator for Pho 79.

  • ​

    Dense & Growing Demographics: The resident population of 18,000+ people within a 5-minute drive of Walmart Way has increased over 20% since 2010 and is expected to grow another 5%+ by 2028.

  • ​

    Diversified Income Stream: The Walmart Way rent roll is comprised of thirty-two tenants of which no tenant occupies more than 7.50% of occupied square footage. 46% of the occupied SF has no remaining lease options providing a landlord with leasing control and the ability to drive rental revenue.

  • ​

    Nearby Mixed-Use Development - Summit Pointe: Summit Pointe is a newly delivered live-work-play community less than a mile from Walmart Way. The $330M development spans 69 acres and upon full completion will consist of 1M SF office space, 500K SF of retail space. 1,400+ residential units, and 250K SF of conference space.

Reedy River Retail at SVN Blackstream and SVN Second Story Commercial have been retained to exclusively offer for sale the leasehold interest in the WestGate Mall in Spartanburg, SC.​ WestGate Mall is well located along Interstate 26 in the Greenville/Spartanburg MSA, widely recongized as one of the fastest growing markets in the country and home to international companies including BMW, Michelin and Milliken.​

As the only enclosed mall in Spartanburg County, WestGate is anchored by Belk, Dillards JCPenny and Costco and sits on ±52 AC with interstate frontage and visibility.​ The sale includes ±431,306 SF of owned GLA as part of a ground lease with options extending through 2084.​ WestGate Mall is currently 82% occupied, presenting an immediate value add opportunity for a qualified buyer.​
column4:
This is a rare opportunity to purchase the leasehold interest in the WestGate Mall, located in one of the hottest markets in the United States. WestGate is the only enclosed mall in Spartanburg County and serves as the primary retail shopping destination for the growing Spartanburg market.

The ±431,306 SF of mall-owned GLA is 82% occupied providing a value add opportunity through lease up of the remaining vacancy. The mall is anchored by JCPenney (lease), Belk (sub-ground lease), Dillards (REA) and Costco (REA). The REA expires 10/31/2066, and the owner of the former Sears property is also a party to the agreement.

High quality inline tenants includes the likes of Rack Room Shoes, Bath & Body Works, H&M, and Victorias Secret.

WestGate Mall boasts visibility to Interstate 26 (±64,000 VPD) and is surrounded by national retailers including Target, Hobby Lobby and Regal Cinemas.

CBRE’s Net Lease Property Group is pleased to present the brand new Class A retail development, Grand Cypress Marketplace located in St.​ Johns (Jacksonville) Florida.​ This is a brand new 43,613 SF (including a 2,000 SF liquor store) freestanding Winn Dixie along with 10,736 SF of Class A shadow anchored retail space.​ The property is ideally located in the high growth affluent Florida market of St.​ Johns where average annual household incomes exceed $125K, and is situated at the entrance to over 1,000 residential units including 844 brand new apartments.​

On August 16, 2023 it was announced that ALDI has entered into a definitive agreement to acquire Winn Dixie and Harveys Supermarket.​ This transaction is expected to close in the first half of 2024 and will increase ALDI's U.​S.​ store count to 2,700 and its footprint by 48% to 60 million square feet.​ In Florida ALDI's store count would more than double to 506 accounting for 19% of all grocery stores in the state -ahead of Walmart at 13% second only to Publix at 32%.​

Jacksonville is the top market in the United States for retail rent growth over the past three years at 28% (CoStar Analytics Aug.​ 29, 2023)

We are excited to present an exceptional business opportunity in the heart of Salem, South Dakota - a well-established and thriving hardware store is now available for sale.​ Whether you're an experienced entrepreneur looking to expand your portfolio or a passionate individual seeking to enter the world of retail, this hardware store offers a solid foundation for your success.​

Here are some remarkable features of this hardware store:

  1. ​

    Prime Location: Situated in the charming town of Salem, SD, our hardware store enjoys a central and easily accessible location.​ Salem's growing community and proximity to larger cities make it an ideal spot for business growth.​

  2. ​

    Established Customer Base: With years of dedicated service, this hardware store has built a loyal customer base within the local community.​ Our reputation for quality products and exceptional customer service sets us apart.​

  3. ​

    Diverse Inventory: The store boasts a comprehensive inventory of hardware, tools, plumbing supplies, electrical equipment, paint, gardening supplies, and much more.​ You'll have everything needed to cater to the diverse needs of our customers.​

  4. ​

    Experienced Staff: Our knowledgeable and experienced staff are committed to helping customers find the right solutions for their projects, ensuring customer satisfaction and loyalty.​

  5. ​

    Growth Potential: Salem's economy is on the rise, and there are ample opportunities for expansion and diversification.​ With the right vision, this hardware store can tap into new markets and increase profitability.​

  6. ​

    Turnkey Operation: The business is well-organized, with efficient operational systems in place.​ The sale includes all assets, fixtures, and equipment, making it a seamless transition for the new owner.​

  7. ​

    Competitive Pricing: We offer competitive pricing and attractive discounts, making us the go-to destination for both DIY enthusiasts and professional contractors.​

If you've ever dreamed of owning a successful hardware store in a welcoming community, this is your chance.​ Salem, SD, is a great place to live and work, and this hardware store is the perfect opportunity to become an integral part of this community while enjoying the rewards of entrepreneurship.​
